To make the white sauce, melt butter in a saucepan over medium heat. Add flour and cook for 2 mins. Gradually whisk in milk. Cook for 5 mins, until sauce is smooth and slightly thickened. Add eggs and Cheddar.
Transfer 1/2 of the pasta to prepared dish. Cover with 1/2 of the ground beef mixture. Repeat. Top with white sauce. Bake for 30-40 mins, until golden. Serve.

title: braided brioche loaf
directions: Combine 2/3 cup lukewarm milk, yeast, and honey in a small bowl and mix to combine. Set aside for 10 minutes.

Combine flour and salt in a large bowl and mix with a wooden spoon. Make a well in the middle of the flour. Pour the milk mixture into the well and stir until combined. Cover and set aside for 15 minutes to rise.

Meanwhile, melt the butter and combine with 1/3 cup of milk. Add butter mixture and the beaten egg to the dough and knead until smooth. Cover, and let rest in a warm place for 45 minutes, or until doubled in size.

Preheat oven to 400°F. Turn dough onto lightly floured surface and cut into 3 equal pieces. Roll each piece to form a rope about 18 inches long. Set ropes side by side and press together at one end. Braid ropes loosely and press ends together. Place on a greased cookie sheet and cover. Leave brioche in a warm place for 30 minutes to rise.
Mix the egg yolk with 1 tsp milk and brush over the brioche. Bake on the middle rack for 30 minutes. After 15-20 minutes cover with foil to prevent burning. Let brioche cool on a wire rack.

title: double chocolate carrot cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Lightly grease an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan. Line with parchment paper.

Sift flour, cocoa powder and spice into a large bowl. Mix in brown sugar, carrot, oil and eggs. Pour into prepared pan. Bake for 40-45 mins, until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 mins. Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack.

For the ganache, heat cream in a small saucepan on medium heat until almost boiling. Remove from heat. Add chocolate and let stand for 5 mins. Stir until smooth. Refrigerate for 15-20 mins, until spreadable.
Cut cooled cake into carrot shape as shown. Halve horizontally. Sandwich with one-quarter of ganache. Spread remaining ganache over top and sides. Refrigerate for 5 mins.

For the icing, knead orange food color into 16 oz of the icing. Roll out between 2 sheets parchment paper until 1/8 inch thick. Lift onto rolling pin and drape over cake. Press around cake. Trim edges. Press skewer on surface to create carrot markings.

Knead green food color into remaining icing. Roll out until 1/8 inch thick as above. Cut into strips. Roll square end of chopstick along strips for frills. Pleat to make leaf shapes. Position at top of cake.

title: individual pizzas
directions: Preheat the oven to 450°F. Place pizza crusts on a baking sheet. Spread pizza sauce evenly on each pizza crust. Top with tomatoes, pepperoni, olives and cheese. Drizzle with pesto.
Bake for 8-10 minutes or until cheese is melted. Top with arugula.

title: roasted tomato soup
directions: Preheat oven to 450°F. Arrange tomatoes, onion and thyme in a large roasting pan lined with foil. Wrap garlic in foil and add to pan. Drizzle olive oil over top of vegetables and season. Roast for 45-50 mins, or until starting to char.
Transfer roasted tomatoes and onion to a heavy-bottomed saucepan along with stock and 1 tsp sugar. Squeeze garlic from skins into pan. Heat through then puree. Add cream and warm through.

title: spaghetti seafood marinara
directions: Cook pasta in a large saucepan of boiling water according to packet directions. Drain; return to pan,
Meanwhile, heat oil in a large, heavy-bottomed saucepan on medium heat. Add onion and garlic; cook, stirring occasionally, for 3 mins.
Increase heat to high. Add wine; boil for 3 mins, until reduced by half. Add pasta sauce; stir well to combine and bring to a boil.

Add mussels; cover and cook, shaking pan frequently, for 3 mins, until mussels have started to open. Add fish and shrimp; cook, uncovered, for 3-4 mins, until just tender. Add sugar and basil. Season to taste and stir gently to combine.
Add sauce to pasta; toss gently to combine. Serve with additional basil leaves.

title: baked orange and passionfruit cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°F. Line an 8 inch springform pan with parchment paper.
In a food processor, process graham crackers to crumbs. Add butter and pulse to combine. Press mixture into base and side of prepared pan. Chill for 30 mins.

Meanwhile, beat cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar and orange zest together until smooth. Beat in 3 tbsp orange juice and flour. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in cream then transfer to prepared pan and place on a baking tray. Bake for 1 hour 10 mins, until just set in the center. Turn oven off and let cool in oven with door ajar (to prevent cracking). Chill overnight.
In a saucepan, combine passionfruit pulp with remaining sugar and orange juice. Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves. Simmer for 4-5 mins, until thickened and syrupy. Let cool slightly.
Arrange orange segments over cheesecake then pour passionfruit syrup over top. Serve with whipped cream.

title: peach and raspberry crumble
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Mix the granulated sugar, butter, flour, pistachios, vanilla and lemon peel in a bowl until crumbly. Refrigerate.
Place the raspberries and drained peaches into an 8-cup baking dish. Sprinkle with brown sugar and drizzle with 3 tbsp lemon juice. Sprinkle with the crumble mixture.
Bake for about 25 mins until golden brown.

title: baked rigatoni with salmon and beets
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Cook pasta in boiling salted water according to package instructions then drain and transfer to an ovenproof baking dish. In a separate pan, gently heat soft cheese, stock, lemon zest and thyme until cheese has melted. Season.

Meanwhile, heat 1 tbsp oil in a frying pan and sear salmon fillet over high heat, remove and set aside. Add shallots and cook for 5 mins then add spinach and cook for 1-2 mins until wilted. Season to taste. Spread spinach over pasta then add cubed beets. Break salmon into pieces and arrange over top. Cover with cheese sauce then add cubed cheese over top. Drizzle with remaining oil and bake for 20-25 mins until cheese is melted and bubbling.

title: potatoes with bacon and chanterelle mushrooms
directions: Heat the oil in a frying pan and fry the bacon. Add the mushrooms and cook for 1-2 mins. Stir in the spring onions and potatoes and season with pepper. Pour in the white wine and stock, bring to a boil, cover and simmer for 8-10 mins. Stir in 2/3 of the Parmesan until it melts. Season to taste, fold in the arugula and sprinkle with the remaining Parmesan. Serve immediately in deep dishes.

title: acorn squash, walnut and zucchini loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease and line a 9x5 inch loaf pan with parchment paper.

Melt butter in a saucepan. Saute squash, celery and onion for 4-5 mins. Add garlic and rosemary. Cook for 1 min. Add barley. Cook for 1 min, tossing to coat. Add wine and cook for 1-2 mins, or until almost absorbed. Add stock, 1 cup at a time, stirring until absorbed. Cover and let cool slightly.
Meanwhile, heat a grill pan over high heat. Lightly coat zucchini with oil. Grill for 1 min per side, or until tender. Line loaf pan with zucchini, slightly overlapping.

Combine nuts, breadcrumbs, Parmesan and eggs with barley. Season. Press firmly into prepared pan, folding excess zucchini over top. Cover with foil and bake for 45 mins. Remove foil and bake another 10-15 mins. Let cool in pan for 10 mins.
Meanwhile, to make the tomato salsa, combine tomato, parsley, oil and lemon juice. Season.
Serve loaf with tomato salsa.

title: peach and red currant crumble
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, 3/4 cup of butter in flakes, 1/3 cup of sugar, 1 pinch of salt, and 1 tsp of vanilla extract in a mixing bowl. Combine ingredients well, then crumble by hand and place in refrigerator to chill.

Cream together 1 3/4 cups of butter, 2 cups of sugar, 1 tsp of vanilla extract and a pinch of salt. Add the eggs one at a time, alternating each time with 1 tbsp of flour and stir well. Mix the remaining flour with the baking powder, add to the mixture and stir briefly.

Preheat the oven to 325°F. Pour the dough into a greased and floured 13 x 15 inch baking dish and smooth surface. Arrange the peach slices and red currants in an alternating pattern on the dough, top with crumble and bake on the middle shelf of the oven for about 25 mins.
Remove cake from oven and allow to cool for about 3 hours. Mix the powdered sugar and lemon juice and drizzle over cake before serving.

title: pumpkin soup with meatballs
directions: Heat butter in a large saucepan and sweat onion until soft. Sprinkle with sugar and let caramelize. Add potatoes, carrots and squash and cook for 5 mins. Season and add nutmeg to taste. Add stock and simmer for 10 mins. Puree and season. Add 1/2 cup creme fraiche (or sour cream, if using). Add meatballs and cook for 10 mins. Serve soup in deep bowls, garnished with pumpkin seeds and remaining creme fraiche.

title: pineapple and mint sorbet
directions: Gently heat 2 cups water and sugar until sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 8-10 mins, without stirring. Allow to cool then add 1 tbsp mint. Combine with pineapple puree, cover and freeze for about 3 hours, until just set.
Whip frozen pineapple mixture and egg whites together until smooth. Transfer to 2 - 11x7 inch baking pans. Cover and freeze overnight, until firm.
Scoop and serve in chilled glasses with chopped pineapple and remaining mint.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°F. In a bowl, combine baking mix, 1/2 cup milk, sour cream and onion salt. Stir until a thick dough forms. Pat dough out into a 3/4 inch thick disc. Cut out 12 biscuits with a 13/4 inch biscuit cutter.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet. Brush tops with remaining milk and bake for 10 mins, or until light golden brown.

title: apple-blackberry crumble with rosemary-orange cream
directions: Gently heat the cream in a saucepan with the rosemary leaves and the orange juice. Remove from the heat and cool then chill in the fridge for 2 hours.

Meanwhile, to make the crumble topping, place the marzipan in a bowl with the butter, egg, 4 tbsp of the sugar and the flour. Stir with a wooden spoon to combine, then rub together with your fingertips to create a crumbled texture. Transfer to the fridge.

Preheat the oven to 400°F. Heat the apples in saucepan with the remaining sugar and 2-3 tbsp water, cover and steam for 5 mins, stirring halfway through. Remove from the heat and gently stir in the blackberries. Divide between 6-8 individual ovenproof dishes or ramekins. Cover with the crumble topping and bake for 20-25 mins.
While the crumble is baking, pour the cream through a fine sieve and beat until softly whipped. Serve with the crumble.

title: yogurt dressing
directions: Combine yogurt, garlic and parsley in a small bowl. Season to taste.

title: old fashioned walnut tea bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Mix the raisins, oatmeal, tea and brown sugar in a large bowl. Let stand for 10 minutes. Mix the flour, baking powder, cinnamon and ginger in a medium bowl. Beat the egg with a pinch of salt. Add to the raisin mixture along with the chopped nuts. Stir in the flour mixture until well blended. Spoon into a greased and floured 4 x 8 inch loaf pan. Sprinkle the top with the reserved chopped nuts.
Bake for 30-40 minutes. Cool for 5 minutes in the pan. Remove from the pan and cool on a wire rack.

title: lemongrass chicken
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°F.
Combine chicken and remaining ingredients in large baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, about 30 mins or until chicken is cooked through, turning chicken once during cooking.

title: watercress salad
directions: Combine pear, and orange peel and juice in large bowl. Cover; refrigerate for 15 mins.
Boil, steam or microwave snow peas until just tender; drain. Rinse under cold water; drain.

For the cheese balls, combine cheeses and herbs in small bowl. Roll teaspoons of mixture into balls. Combine curry powder and paprika in small bowl; gently toss half of the cheese balls in spice mixture until coated.
Add snow peas and watercress to pear mixture; toss gently. Serve topped with cheese balls.

title: smoked ham with creamy cabbage and bacon
directions: Heat 1 tbsp oil in a saucepan, add the bacon and fry for 3-4 mins. Add the cabbage and saute for 2-3 mins. Then season and stir in the nutmeg and 2/3 cup vegetable stock. Simmer for 15-20 mins, until tender.

Meanwhile, melt the butter in a separate saucepan, stir in the flour until smooth then gradually stir in 1/2 cup of stock and the milk. Bring to a boil then simmer, stirring, for 4-5 mins until thickened. Mix into the cabbage and keep warm.
Coat the onions in 2 tbsp flour and tap off any excess. Heat 1 tbsp oil in a frying pan, add the onions and saute for 3-5 mins until crisp, then remove from the pan and keep warm.

Add 1 tbsp oil to the pan, followed by the slices of ham. Fry for 4-6 mins, turning, until cooked through. To serve, divide the cabbage between 4 plates, place a slice of ham on top and drizzle with extra sauce.

title: crispy polenta with mixed vegetables and gorgonzola
directions: Heat 2 tbsp oil in a large pan. Add polenta and cook for 2-3 mins per side, until golden. Set aside and keep warm. Add bacon and cook, stirring, for 3-5 mins. Add zucchini and remaining oil. Cook for 5-8 mins, until browned.

Preheat broiler. Return polenta to pan along with tomatoes. Broil for 2-3 mins, until tomatoes have softened. Sprinkled with cheese and broil for another 1-2 mins, until cheese is melted and bubbling. Season. Serve immediately with arugula salad.

title: walnut coffee creams
directions: Preheat the oven to 300°F. Lightly grease 2 baking pans and line with parchment paper. Combine coffee and 1 tbsp boiling water in a small bowl, stirring to dissolve.
Beat butter and powdered sugar in a large bowl with an electric mixer until creamy. Beat in coffee mixture. Lightly fold in combined sifted flour and custard powder.

Roll tablespoons of mixture into balls and arrange on prepared pans, 1 inch apart. Flatten slightly and push a walnut into half the cookies. Bake for 20-25 mins, until golden. Cool in pan 2 mins. Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack.

Meanwhile, for the filling, dissolve coffee in 2 tsp boiling water and set aside. Beat butter in a medium bowl with electric mixer until pale. Gradually add powdered sugar, beating until smooth. Beat in coffee. Spread on flat side of plain cookies. Sandwich together with remaining cookies, walnut-side up.

title: swiss chard and strawberry salad
directions: Whisk vinegar, oil, poppy seeds and sugar in a small bowl. Season to taste. Cover and set aside overnight.
Combine chard and strawberries in a large serving bowl. Drizzle with dressing and toss to combine. Serve.

title: salmon, pea and cream fettuccine
directions: Cook fettuccine in boiling, salted water for 2 mins or until al dente. Drain.

Meanwhile, combine cream, lemon juice and zest in a large frying pan over medium heat. Cook, stirring, for 1-2 mins, until just simmering. Add peas, salmon and fettuccine. Toss well then add spring onions and season to taste. Serve with freshly ground black pepper.

title: salmon pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F.
To make the pastry dough, cut 8 tbsp butter into 1 2/3 cups flour with a pinch of salt. Add cheese and chervil. Add 3 tbsp cold water and mix until just combined. Chill.
Meanwhile, to make the filling, blanch leek, celery, peas and fava beans in boiling salted water for 5 mins. Drain.

Cook salmon in remaining butter for 5 mins. Remove from pan and set aside. Add remaining flour and cook for 1 min, stirring. Gradually whisk in milk and cream. Bring to a boil, stirring, until thickened. Add salmon, vegetables, dill and spinach. Season then transfer to a pie dish.
Roll out pastry and cover top of dish. Brush with egg and bake for 35 mins, until golden brown.

title: mini beef and guinness pies
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan on high heat. Cook beef, stirring, until browned. Add onion; cook, stirring, until softened. Add flour; cook, stirring, until mixture bubbles and is well browned.

Gradually add stout and stock, stirring until gravy boils and thickens. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, 1 hour. Uncover; simmer, stirring occasionally, 30 mins. Cool filling 10 mins then refrigerate until cold.
Preheat the oven to 425°F. Lightly grease three 12-cup mini muffin pans.

Lightly roll out pie crusts on floured surface. Using 2 1/3-inch pastry cutter, cut 36 rounds from pie crusts. Pace 1 round in each of the muffin cup. Using 2-inch pastry cutter, cut 36 rounds from remaining pie crusts.

Spoon 1 heaping tsp of the cold filling into each crust. Brush around edges with beaten egg. Top each pie with smaller pastry round. Press gently around edge to seal; brush with remaining egg. Using sharp knife, make two small slits in top of each pie.
Bake pies about 15 mins or until lightly browned. Cool in pan 5 mins. Remove from pan; place on serving platters.

title: salmon confit with herb salad
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Roast pepper for 30 mins, or until skin blisters and blackens. Cover with plastic wrap and let stand for 5 min. Peel, discard seeds and membrane then slice flesh thinly.

Reduce oven to 250°F. Arrange fennel and leek, cut-side down, in a single layer in a large baking dish. Add garlic, bay leaf and olive oils. Cover with baking paper and bake for 1 hour, or tender. Remove vegetables from dish with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.

Reduce oven to 200°F. Submerge salmon, skin-side down, in oil in dish. Cover with baking paper and bake for 2 hours 30 mins, or until salmon is heated through, but still looks glassy. Remove salmon and drain on paper towels.
For the herb salad, combine herbs in a medium serving bowl. Whisk together lemon juice and olive oil in a small bowl. Season to taste. Set aside.

For the dill mayonnaise, combine egg yolks, lemon juice and mustard in a blender and blend until smooth. With the motor running, gradually add oil in a thin, steady stream. Blend until thick. Stir in 2 tbsp dill and season to taste. Thin with water or more lemon juice if necessary.
Dress herb salad with lemon vinaigrette. Serve salmon topped with vegetables, herb salad and dill mayonnaise.

title: chocolate tart with cranberries and nuts
directions: Combine flour, powdered sugar and egg with a pinch of salt. Cut in 1/2 cup cold, cubed butter then gently knead until smooth. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill for 30 mins.

Preheat oven to 325°F. Roll out dough then use to line a greased 7 x 11 inch loose-bottomed tart pan. Prick base with a fork, cover with a piece of parchment paper, fill with pie weights and bake for 20 mins. Remove beans and bake for another 15 mins. Allow to cool.

Meanwhile, heat cream, add chocolate and remaining butter and cook, stirring, over low heat until chocolate melts. Allow to cool for 10 mins then transfer to tart pan. Top with dried fruit and chopped nuts. Chill for 30 mins before serving.

title: red snapper with avocado salad
directions: Mix the vinegar with 1 chopped onion and season with salt, pepper and sugar. Beat in 3 tbsp of the oil. Place the lettuce, avocado and tomatoes in a bowl and drizzle with the vinaigrette.

Mix the remaining onion with the garlic, basil, paprika, 1 tsp salt, cayenne pepper and thyme. Melt the butter and mix in a bowl with the remaining olive oil. Dip the fish in the oil and butter mixture, and press down in the spice mixture. Cook in a skillet for 3-4 mins on each side. Serve with the salad, garnished with grapefruit slices and basil leaves.

title: baby arugula and parmesan salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large serving bowl. Season and toss combine. Serve.

title: pumpkin & potato soup
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan and saute onion, garlic and chilies. Add pumpkin and potatoes. Pour in stock and orange juice, and bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover, and simmer for 20 mins. Meanwhile, toast pumpkin seeds in a dry pan. Remove and cool.
Remove soup from the heat. Take out a few pieces of pumpkin with a slotted spoon and set aside. Puree soup finely, and season.
Serve in deep soup bowls and add pumpkin pieces and toasted pumpkin seeds. Garnish with creme fraiche and orange zest.

title: marinated shrimp with pineapple salsa
directions: Combine lemongrass, chili and coriander in a mortar and pound with the pestle until a paste forms. Transfer to a bowl and stir in coconut milk.
Arrange shrimp in a shallow dish. Pour over marinade, turning to coat. Chill, covered, 2 hours.
Meanwhile, to make salsa: In a large bowl, combine all salsa ingredients except peanuts. Chill until required. Add peanuts just before serving.
Thread each shrimp lengthwise on a skewer. Preheat a grill or grill pan on medium. Brush lightly with oil. Cook shrimp for 4-5 minutes, turning, until just cooked through. Serve with salsa.

title: turkey schnitzel pizzaiola
directions: Mix the garlic and 3 tsp lime juice and apply to turkey cutlets as a marinade.

Heat 1 tbsp of olive oil and saute the onion briefly. Stir in the tomato puree, add the tomatoes and season to taste. Pour in the stock, add the olives, rosemary and basil and simmer for about 10 mins. Add 1 tsp lime juice.
Cook the tagliatelle in boiling salted water for about 8 mins.
Heat 1 tbsp of olive oil and fry turkey cutlets for about 2 mins on each side. Season to taste. Serve the pasta, turkey and sauce, garnished with slices of lime and fresh herbs.

title: curried mussel and rice soup
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan on high heat. Saute onion and garlic for 2-3 mins, until onion is tender. Add curry paste; cook, stirring, for 1 min.
Add rice; saute for 1 min. Stir in stock and lemon juice. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer for 12-15 mins, until rice is tender.
Stir in mussels. Cover pan and cook for 3-5 mins. Discard any unopened mussels.
Add green beans; simmer for 1 min. Serve topped with cilantro and chili pepper.

title: coconut chocolate crunchies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Grease and line baking pans with parchment paper.
Beat butter, sugar and syrup in a large bowl with an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Fold in sifted flour, and coconut and oats.

Roll rounded teaspoons of mixture into balls. Place 2 inches apart on prepared pans; flatten with the palm of your hand until 1 1/2-inch round. Using a flour-dusted fork, mark cookies. Bake 12 mins. Cool in pans 2 mins. Remove from pans; cool completely on wire rack.

Meanwhile, for the chocolate ganache filling, stir chocolate and butter in a small heatproof bowl over a small saucepan of simmering water until smooth (don't let water touch bottom of bowl). Cool ganache until spreadable.
Sandwich two cookies with 2 tsp ganache. Let stand until filling is firm.

title: potato and ground beef casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Grease a 7 x 10 inch baking dish. Heat the oil in a large saucepan and cook the ground beef, stirring, for 8-10 mins, until browned and crumbly. Season then add the celery, carrots, onion and garlic and saute for 2 mins. Stir in the tomato paste, then pour in the wine and tomatoes. Season then simmer over medium heat for 30 mins, stirring occasionally. Reserve a little basil for garnish and stir in the remainder.

Arrange 1/3 of the potato slices in the bottom of the dish. Cover with 1/2 the Bolognese sauce. Layer another 1/3 of the potatoes then the remaining Bolognese and finish with the remaining potatoes. Sprinkle with mozzarella and bake for 50-60 mins, until golden and bubbling, covering with foil after 40 mins if it is browning too quickly. Sprinkle with the remaining basil to serve.

title: baked creamy pea pots
directions: Preheat the oven to 300°F. Cook the peas in a pan of lightly salted boiling water for 5-6 mins until tender. Drain and place in a food processor with the milk and half the cream. Process to a smooth puree.

Add the egg yolks, mint and remaining cream and season with salt and freshly ground black pepper. Divide the mixture between six small buttered ramekins. Cover with foil and place in a roasting pan and pour in enough water to come halfway up the sides of the dishes. Bake for 1 hour until set then remove from the pan and leave to cool. Chill for 1 hour.
Sprinkle the Parmesan cheese over the ramekins and place under a preheated broiler for a few mins until the cheese turns golden. Serve garnished with mint sprigs.

title: hawaiian toast
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Heat oil in a pan and sear pork for about 2 mins per side. Season then set aside. Add carrots and cook for 3 mins. Add apricots and almonds and cook for another 3 mins. Season then add jam and remove from heat.
Place bread on a lined baking sheet. Top with pork and apricot mixture. Sprinkle with cheese and bake for about 15 mins. Serve sprinkled with parsley.

title: classic fruit tart
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Lightly grease a 9 inch loose-bottom tart pan.

Sift flour into a large bowl. Add sugar. Cut in butter until mixture resembles breadcrumbs. Add 1/4 cup water, egg yolk and lemon juice. Mix until smooth then knead lightly. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill for 30 mins.

Roll dough out until 1/8 inch thick and use to line pan. Trim edges. Chill for 10 mins. Reduce heat to 350°F. Line tart shell with parchment paper and pie weights. Blind bake for 10-15 mins. Remove paper and weights and bake for another 10-15 mins, until golden brown.

Meanwhile, for the filling, bring milk and vanilla bean paste to a boil. Whisk together egg yolks and sugar until thick and pale. Add cornstarch and flour then whisk in milk mixture. Return to saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until custard boils and thickens. Simmer, stirring, for 2 mins. Cover with plastic wrap and let cool to room temperature. Transfer to tart shell and arrange fruit over top. Chill until ready to serve.

title: coconut and lemon syrup cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Grease a deep 8-inch round cake pan; line bottom and side with parchment paper.

Beat butter and sugar in a large bowl with an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Fold in 1 3/4 cups coconut and sifted flour. Spoon into prepared pan. Sprinkle with remaining 2 tbsp coconut.
Bake about 50 mins until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.

Meanwhile, for the lemon syrup, stir sugar, 1 cup water and lemon peel in a small saucepan on medium heat, without boiling, until sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, without stirring, 5 mins. Strain.
Pour hot lemon syrup over hot cake in pan. Cool cake in pan.

title: cranberry and cinnamon jam
directions: Place the cranberries, sugar, cinnamon sticks and 1 cup water in a heavy-based saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally until sugar has dissolved. Reduce heat and simmer 20 mins, or until thickened. Remove cinnamon sticks. Pour hot jam into sterilized glass jars and screw lids on tightly. Turn jars upside down and cool completely.

title: seared fish with lemon beurre blanc
directions: For the lemon beurre blanc, place wine, onion and peppercorns in a medium saucepan on medium heat. Cook for 10-12 mins, until liquid reduces to about 2 tbsp. Strain and discard solids.

Clean saucepan and return liquid. Heat on medium heat. Add butter a little at a time, whisking until sauce is creamy and slightly thickened. Remove from heat and whisk in lemon juice to taste. Season to taste.

Heat a large skillet on high heat. Brush fish with melted butter and season to taste. Place, skin-side down, in pan and cook for 2-3 mins. Turn and cook for a further 1-2 mins, until just cooked through.
Serve fish drizzled with beurre blanc and accompany with steamed beans.

title: grilled ham and peach salad
directions: Brush a grill pan with oil and heat on high. Cook the peaches, cut-side down for 1-2 mins. Cook the ham in batches for 2-3 mins each side, until charred. When cool enough to handle, tear into bite-size pieces.
Arrange the lettuce leaves, peaches and ham on serving plates and sprinkle with the pistachios. Whisk the dressing ingredients and season to taste. Drizzle the dressing over the salad and serve.

title: caramel chocolate bars
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Lightly grease a 12 x 8-inch baking pan and line with parchment paper.
Melt 8 tbsp (1 stick) of the butter in a large bowl. Stir in flour, coconut and sugar until combined. Press mixture firmly into bottom of prepared pan. Bake for 10-15 mins, or until lightly golden.
Meanwhile, combine sweetened condensed milk, remaining 2 tbsp butter and syrup in a small saucepan on low heat. Stir, without boiling, for 10-15 mins, until mixture is golden brown.
Pour hot filling over crust. Bake for 10 mins. Cool on a wire rack.
Combine chocolate and shortening in a small saucepan on low heat. Stir until melted and smooth. Spread over filling. Let stand at room temperature until set. Cut into squares.

title: french bread pizzas
directions: Prepare the baguettes according to the package instructions. Heat the oil in a small pan and saute the shallots. Add the tomato puree, then pour in the stock and simmer for 10 mins. Add the chili powder, dried thyme and oregano and season to taste.
Preheat the oven to 400°F. Cut the baguettes in half lengthways and spread them evenly with the sauce, chopped salami and corn. Sprinkle with cheese and bake for about 6 mins.

title: bacon and herb chicken patties
directions: Combine garlic, onions, chicken, egg, breadcrumbs, herbs and chutney in a large bowl. Season then shape into 8 patties. Wrap each patty with bacon and place on a tray. Cover and chill for 30 mins.
Oil a large frying pan and place over medium heat. Cook chicken patties until browned on both sides and cooked through. Serve.

title: lasagne with bolognese sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Heat 2 tbsp olive oil in a large pan and fry bacon until crispy. Remove bacon, add ground beef to pan and cook until browned. Add carrots, celery and onions. Stir in tomato puree and reserved tomato juice. Return bacon to pan and add tomatoes, crushing with a spoon. Add herbs and season to taste. Simmer for 10 mins.
Heat butter in a saucepan, add flour and stir until browned. Add stock, milk and cream. Bring to a boil, add half the Parmesan and stir to combine. Add nutmeg and white pepper and season to taste.

Grease a large baking dish. Spread one quarter of Bechamel sauce over base of dish and cover with 3 lasagne sheets. Spoon half of Bolognese sauce over the sheets. Top with 3 more sheets of lasagne and one quarter of remaining Bolognese and Bechamel. Layer 3 more lasagne sheets and remaining Bolognese sauce. Finish with remaining lasagne sheets and Bechamel.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan and bake for about 40 minutes, until golden brown.

title: bbq chicken noodle soup
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan over medium heat. Saute onion 4-5 mins, until tender. Stir in chicken stock and creamed corn. Bring to a boil on high. Add noodles and cook 8-10 mins, until noodles are tender. Stir in chicken. Cook 1 min and season to taste. Garnish with chives and serve.

title: waffles with cream
directions: Lightly grease and preheat a waffle iron. For the batter, cream the butter with the sugar, the vanilla extract and the salt. Whisk in the eggs one at a time. Mix the whipping cream and milk together in a bowl. In a separate bowl, stir the baking powder into the flour. Gradually whisk the cream mixture into the egg mixture, alternating with the flour and baking powder mixture, until all are combined. Use the batter to make 8 waffles. Cover and chill any remaining batter. It will keep for up to 3 days in the fridge.
For the filling, whisk the wine into the mascarpone and serve sandwiched between two waffles. Decorate with caramel strands and sugared rose petals, if using.

title: hazelnut chocolate cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Grease and line the base and sides of an 8 inch round cake pan.

Put the 1 1/3 cups butter, sugar and vanilla bean paste into a medium bowl. Beat with an electric mixer until pale and creamy. On a low speed, add the beaten egg, a little at a time, alternating with a spoonful of flour. Gradually add 1/2 cup milk, then the remaining flour, hazelnuts, 1/3 cup cocoa powder and salt.
Spread the batter into the prepared pan and smooth the top with a flat knife. Bake for 50-60 mins, or until a skewer inserted into the middle of the cake comes out clean.
Cool the cake in the pan for 10 mins, then turn it out onto a wire rack to cool completely,

To make the icing, place 6 tbsp butter, 2 tbsp milk and 2 tbsp cocoa powder into a small bowl and mix together. Slowly add the powdered sugar, in small batches, beating well with a wooden spoon. Spread the cake with the chocolate icing and serve.

title: lemon and dill risotto cakes
directions: Place stock and 3 cups water in medium saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer.

Meanwhile, heat oil in large saucepan on medium heat. Cook onion and garlic, stirring, until soft. Add rice; stir to coat rice in onion mixture. Add wine; cook, stirring, until liquid is absorbed. Add 1/2 cup of the simmering stock; cook, stirring, on low heat until stock is absorbed. Continue adding stock, in 1/2-cup batches, stirring, until stock is absorbed after each addition. Total cooking time should be about 35 mins or until rice is tender. Stir in lemon peel and dill. Cool risotto 10 mins. Cover; refrigerate 2 hours.
For the lemon dill dressing, whisk all ingredients in small bowl.
Shape risotto into 18 risotto cakes. Heat large, lightly oiled skillet on medium heat. Cook cakes, in batches, until lightly browned both sides. Cover to keep warm.
Cook radicchio, stirring, in same pan until just wilted.
Drizzle risotto cakes and radicchio with dressing.

title: vegetable salad with yogurt dressing
directions: To make the yogurt dressing, whisk together yogurt, green onion and lemon juice. Season.
For the salad, steam or boil vegetables, separately, until just tender. Drain and combine with white beans. Add yogurt dressing and toss to combine. Top with chopped hard-boiled eggs.

title: banana fritters with honey
directions: Sift 1 cup flour and baking powder into a large bowl. Whisk in 1 1/4 cups chilled water until smooth. Let stand for 10 mins.
Meanwhile, fill a large saucepan or wok with 1 inch of oil and heat to 350°F.

Working in batches, dust bananas in remaining flour, shaking off excess. Dip in batter then deep-fry for 3-4 mins, until golden brown. Remove with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels. Serve immediately with honey and heavy cream.

title: plum and apple chutney
directions: Place all ingredients in a large, heavy-bottomed saucepan. Bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer, stirring regularly, for 1 hour, until thick and syrupy.

title: sweet potato and rosemary risotto
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F.
Place sweet potatoes on a large baking tray in a single layer. Drizzle with 1 tbsp oil and season. Bake for 20 mins, or until tender. Set aside.
Meanwhile, place prosciutto on a baking tray and bake for 8 mins, or until crisp. Let cool slightly then break into large pieces.

Heat butter and remaining oil in a large, heavy-bottomed saucepan over medium heat. Add onion and garlic. Cook for 5 mins, or until soft. Add rosemary and rice. Cook for 1 min, stirring, or until grains are well coated. Add wine. Cook for 2-3 mins, or until reduced slightly. Add a ladle of hot stock and stir continuously until liquid is completely absorbed. Continue adding stock, 1 ladle at a time, until rice is tender, about 20-25 mins.
Add sweet potatoes. Add Parmesan and arugula and stir to combine. Remove from heat. Season.
Distribute between shallow serving bowls. Serve immediately topped with prosciutto and extra Parmesan.

title: grilled salmon with yogurt and dill
directions: Heat oil in a large frying pan over high heat. Sprinkle salmon with seasoning and cook for 3-4 mins per side, or until cooked to your liking.
Meanwhile, combine yogurt, dill, lemon juice and garlic. Season to taste. Drizzle over salmon and serve with mixed greens.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F. Lightly grease a baking dish.

In a large frying pan, melt 2 tbsp butter over medium heat. Cook shallot for 3-5 mins, until softened. Add spinach and cook, tossing, for 5 mins, until wilted. Remove spinach from pan, reserving liquid.

Add remaining butter to pan. Once melted, add flour and cook for 2 mins, stirring occasionally. Whisk in milk until smooth then add heavy cream, nutmeg, Parmesan, spinach and reserved liquid. Season. Transfer to prepared baking dish and bake for 15 mins, or until mixture bubbles.
Preheat broiler. Sprinkle breadcrumbs over spinach mixture then broil until golden brown and crunchy.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Heat the olive oil over medium heat in a large skillet and cook the onion and garlic for 10 mins. Add the ground beef and cook over a high heat until browned all over. Stir in the chopped tomatoes, tomato paste, zucchini, carrots, celery, leek and dried oregano and bring to the boil. Cover and simmer for 10 mins until the vegetables are just tender. Season to taste with salt and freshly ground black pepper.

To make the white sauce, Melt the butter in a pan then stir in the flour and cook for 1 min. Gradually whisk in the milk and stock and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat and simmer, stirring, for 5 mins until thickened. Add the nutmeg and season to taste. Preheat the oven to 400°F.

Spread a thin layer of the meat sauce in the base of deep ovenproof dish. Cover with 3 lasagne sheets then repeat the layers two more times ending with lasagne sheets. Spoon over the white sauce and scatter over the cheese. Bake for 45 mins until golden and bubbling. Serve garnished with fresh oregano.

title: veal goulash with fettuccine
directions: Heat half the oil in a large, heavy-bottomed saucepan on medium-high heat. Cook veal in batches for 3-4 mins, until browned. Remove from pan.
Heat remaining oil in same pan on low heat. Saute onion, carrot and garlic for 5 mins, until soft and lightly golden.
Stir in paprika and cook for 1 min. Add tomato paste, stock and veal. Bring to a boil on high heat. Reduce heat to low; simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours. Uncover for last 15 mins to thicken sauce.
Cook fettuccine according to package directions. Drain well. Serve topped with veal goulash and sour cream.

title: grilled vegetable gratin
directions: Preheat broiler. Combine oil, chili flakes and garlic then brush over vegetables. Cook vegetables until browned and tender. Cover and set aside.
Meanwhile, combine 2/3 cup tomato sauce with cannellini beans and heat until warm. Cover and set aside.

In 4 ovenproof serving dishes, layer 1/2 the eggplant, zucchini, mushrooms and bean mixture. Top with remaining eggplant and reserved pasta sauce. Sprinkle with cheese. Broil for 3 mins, or until cheese is melted and browned lightly. Garnish with basil and serve.

title: spinach ricotta and tomato pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Lightly grease an 8-inch round baking dish. Brush each sheet of phyllo with butter; fold in half and brush again. Line prepared dish with phyllo, overlapping the sheets. Bake 10 mins.
Meanwhile, beat eggs and ricotta cheese in a large bowl. Season to taste. Stir in spinach and 1/2 the prosciutto. Pour over phyllo crust. Arrange tomatoes and remaining prosciutto on top.
Bake 30-35 mins, until set. Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: chicken and squash risotto
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Toss squash with rosemary and 1 tbsp oil. Bake for 25 mins, or until golden and tender.

Meanwhile, heat remaining oil in a large Dutch oven. Sweat onion and garlic for 5 mins, or until soft. Add rice and cook for 1 min, until coated. Add wine, 4 cups water and crumbled bouillon cubes. Bring to a boil, cover and bake for 18-20 mins, or until liquid is almost absorbed. Add chicken and cook until heated through.
Add 1/2 arugula, 2.5 oz Parmesan, 1 tsp lemon zest and most of the squash. Serve topped with remaining squash, lemon zest, Parmesan, arugula and lemon wedges.

title: coconut stars
directions: Grease a foil lined 11 x 7 inch baking pan, extending the foil at the long sides to create handles.

Mix the condensed milk, coconut, sugar and vanilla in a medium bowl. Spoon into the prepared pan, pressing into the corners; smooth the surface with a spatula. Refrigerate for 1 hour to set. Meanwhile, melt the chocolate in a heat-proof bowl over a pan of simmering water (do not allow the bowl to touch the water).

Lift the dessert out of the pan using the foil handles. Using a 2 1/2 in star cookie cutter, cut out star shapes. Spread the white chocolate on the top of the stars then sprinkle with the cake decorations. Let stand until chocolate is firm.

title: spanish eggs
directions: In a large frying pan, heat oil over medium heat. Saute red onion for 3-4 mins, until tender. Add chorizo and cook for 4-5 mins, until crispy. Add diced tomatoes and Tabasco. Season to taste. Simmer for 3-4 mins, until sauce thickens slightly.
Using the back of a spoon, make 4 indentations in sauce and carefully break an egg into each. Reduce heat to low and cook, covered, for 5-8 mins, until eggs are cooked to your liking.
Top with green onions and serve with crusty bread.

title: greek salad with lavash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Line 2 baking trays with parchment paper.
Brush 1 side of bread with oil then sprinkle with mint and salt. Cut each piece into 8 wedges then transfer to prepared trays. Bake for 10 mins, until golden and crisp.
In a large bowl, combine tomatoes, olives, cucumbers, pepper and feta. Set aside.
To make the dressing, combine all ingredients in a food processor and process until smooth. Season. Add to salad and toss to combine. Serve with lavash chips.

title: roman chicken and pepper stew
directions: Heat oil in a Dutch oven on medium-high heat. Brown chicken, in batches, for 3 mins each side. Return all chicken pieces to pan with garlic and wine. Cook for 1 min.
Add potato, red peppers and onion and reduce heat to low. Cover and cook for 20 mins until potato is almost tender, adding a little more water during cooking if necessary.
Add olives and season to taste. Cook 5 mins, until chicken is cooked and potatoes are tender. Sprinkle with basil leaves and serve.

title: ricotta and sweet potato cannelloni
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Lightly grease a 9-inch square baking dish.
Heat oil in a medium skillet on low heat. Saute leek 3-5 mins, until softened but not browned. Transfer to a bowl. Add ricotta, sweet potato, spinach and nutmeg to bowl. Season to taste.
Spoon rounded 1/4 cupfuls of mixture onto each lasagne noodle and roll up to form cannelloni. Arrange in a single layer in prepared dish.
Pour tomato puree over cannelloni; top with basil. Cover with cream. Sprinkle with combined mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses
Bake 20-25 mins, until cannelloni is tender and cheese is golden.

title: veal and prosciutto rolls
directions: Lay prosciutto out on a clean work surface. Top each slice of prosciutto with a veal steak. Place a piece of cheese at 1 end of each steak and roll up. Secure with toothpicks.

In a large frying pan, heat oil over high heat. Cook rolls for 6-8 mins, turning, or until browned and cooked to your liking. Set aside and keep warm. Add tomatoes and saute for 2-3 mins, until they begin to collapse, drizzling with extra olive oil if necessary. Season. Serve with veal rolls and baby arugula.

title: blackberry parfait with almond and shortbread crust
directions: Whisk eggs, powdered sugar and 2 tbsp hot water over a hot water bath until thick and creamy. Remove from heat and whisk until cool. Puree blackberries and lemon juice. Add egg mixture. Whip 1 1/4 cups heavy cream until stiff then fold in. Transfer to a 10 x 4 1/2 inch loaf pan lined with plastic wrap and freeze for 30 mins.
Meanwhile, combine shortbread crumbs and almonds. Melt butter and coat crumbs. Gently press onto the chilled parfait. Freeze for at least 5 1/2 hours, or overnight.

To serve, heat remaining cream and chocolate until melted then set aside to cool. Remove parfait from freezer, remove from loaf pan and place on a serving plate, crust-side down. Pour melted chocolate over parfait and serve.

title: zucchini and rice tart
directions: Grease a foil-lined 9 inch springform pan; place on a baking pan. Cook rice in a large saucepan of boiling water for 30 mins or until tender. Rinse under cold water; drain well.

Preheat the oven to 350°F. Heat oil in a large skillet on medium heat. Add onion and cinnamon; cook and stir for 5 mins or until onion softens. Add zucchini; cook and stir for 5 mins. Stir in spinach. Transfer mixture to a large bowl. Stir in dill, lemon peel, feta, olives, rice and egg until well combined. Pour mixture into prepared pan; smooth the top.
Bake for 35-40 mins or until golden. Let stand for 10 mins. Cut into wedges to serve.

title: chocolate sour cream cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Grease and line a 9-inch round cake pan with parchment paper.

Place sugar, butter, 1/3 cup water, cocoa powder and baking soda in a medium saucepan on medium heat. Stir until sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 2 mins. Transfer to a large bowl and cool for 15 mins.
Whisk flour and eggs into chocolate mixture until smooth. Spoon into prepared pan, smoothing top.
Bake for 50 to 60 mins or until a toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pan for 5 mins. Remove from pan; cool completely on a wire rack.

For the frosting, place chocolate, butter, sour cream and sifted powdered sugar in a medium heatproof bowl over a saucepan of simmering water (do not let bowl touch water). Stir until chocolate melts and frosting is smooth. Remove bowl from heat; cool slightly. Chill, stirring occasionally, for 15 mins or until it reaches a spreading consistency. Spread frosting over top and sides of cake. Decorate with chocolate curls.

title: corn fritters with black-eyed pea and pepper salad
directions: In a large bowl, prepare salad dressing by mixing the cilantro, garlic, a teaspoon of lime zest, a teaspoon of lime juice and the red wine vinegar. Add 1 tsp sugar and season to taste. On a serving dish, layer the peas, red pepper, onion, green beans and a third of the sweetcorn on a serving dish, and drizzle over the dressing.

In a separate bowl, mix the flour, cornmeal, baking powder and the rest of the sugar. Add the eggs, milk, chives, chili and the remaining corn. Season to taste and mix well to create a batter. Heat a quarter of the oil in a pan. Drop individual spoonfuls of the batter into the pan to create small fritters. Cook until lightly browned on both sides and firm in the center. Repeat with remaining oil and batter. Serve immediately with the salad on the side.

title: swiss chard salad with quails eggs
directions: Cook the quail eggs in a pot of boiling water for 3 mins then drain and run under cold water for 5 mins. Peel and cut each egg in 1/2.
Mix the orange zest and juice with the yogurt, honey and mustard and season. Toss with the salad greens then place on 4 serving plates. Top with the eggs. Serve with crusty bread.

title: tortellini bake
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Cook the tortellini according to the package directions, drain and set aside.

Meanwhile, for the sauce, heat the butter in a saucepan and stir in the flour. Add the milk and stock a little at a time, stirring constantly until smooth. Add a pinch of nutmeg and the gorgonzola cheese and mix well.
Mix the tortellini, vegetables and cheese sauce together then transfer to a greased baking dish. Sprinkle with mozzarella and bake for about 30 mins until golden brown.

title: salmon coulibiac
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°F. Line a baking pan with parchment paper.
Combine rice, salmon, eggs, onion, capers, dill and lemon juice in large bowl. Season to taste.
Place half salmon mixture along one end of each sheet of pastry. Fold in sides and roll up to enclose. Place on prepared pan, seam side down.
Using a small sharp knife, pierce top of pastry to allow steam to escape. Brush with egg and sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Bake 20-25 mins, until pastry is golden. Serve with spinach leaves.

title: pork and veal sang choy bow
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Cook onion and garlic, stirring, until onion is soft. Add ground meat and cook, stirring, until well browned. Add soy sauce and oyster sauce. Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 5 mins.
Just before serving, stir in bean sprouts, fried noodles, green onions and sesame seeds. Distribute between lettuce leaves and serve.

title: festive brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Lightly grease and line an 8 x 12 inch rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper. Melt butter and 7 oz dark chocolate over low heat. Set aside and let cool slightly. Meanwhile, sift flour and cocoa powder. Add sugar, nuts, Turkish delight, remaining chocolates and cherries. Fold in eggs, sour cream, vanilla extract and chocolate-butter mixture. Transfer to prepared pan and bake for 30-35 mins, or until a skewer comes out clean. Allow to cool in pan before cutting into squares and serving.

title: cheddar and thyme twists
directions: Sift flours into a bowl. Coarsely grate butter over flour, then stir in thyme. Stir in 2/3 cup iced water until mixture starts to come together. Knead for 1 min or until dough forms.

Scrape dough onto a lightly floured surface. Divide dough in half. Roll out each piece to a 12 x 8 inch rectangle. Sprinkle with half the cheese, pressing cheese into the dough. Fold in half to enclose filling. Reroll dough to a 16 x 6 inch rectangle. Repeat with remaining dough and cheese.
Cut dough crosswise into 3/4 inch strips. Twist strips. Transfer to 2 baking sheets lined with parchment paper. Refrigerate for 30 mins.
Preheat the oven to 375°F. Bake for 20 mins or until golden and crisp, swapping trays halfway through cooking.

title: chocolate striped ice cream cones
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease a baking sheet and line with parchment paper. Mark 10 circles on paper.
In a small bowl, beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Gradually add sugar, beating until dissolved between additions. Stir in flour, butter and vanilla.
Place 2 tbsp mixture in a small bowl and stir in cocoa. Spoon into a piping bag fitted with a small, plain nozzle.
Place a level tablespoon of remaining mixture in center of each circle on baking sheet and spread evenly to fill circles. Pipe chocolate stripes across circles.
Bake for 5 mins. Working quickly, lift from tray and shape into cones. Cool on wire racks.
Fill with scoops of ice cream and serve.

title: lemon delicious pudding cakes
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Lightly grease four 1-cup ramekins.
Beat butter and granulated sugar in a large bowl with an electric mixer until combined. Mix in flour and lemon peel.
Whisk lemon juice, milk and egg yolks in a medium bowl. Fold into butter mixture.
Beat egg whites in a clean medium bowl with an electric mixer until soft peaks form. Gently fold into batter. Divide batter evenly among ramekins.
Place ramekins in a large baking dish. Pour in enough hot water into baking dish to come halfway up the sides of ramekins.
Bake, uncovered, 20-25 mins, until firm. Dust with powdered sugar and serve with whipped cream.

title: spiced coconut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease and line an 11x8 inch baking pan with parchment paper, extending paper over long sides for handles.

In a food processor, combine flour, sugar, coconut and spice mix. Process until combined. Add carrot, pineapple, eggs and oil and process for 80 seconds, or until just combined. Transfer to prepared pan and bake for 1 hour 10 mins, or until a skewer inserted in the center comes out clean. Let cool in pan for 15 mins then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.
Meanwhile, to make the cream cheese frosting, in a stand mixer, beat cream cheese, butter and orange zest until light and creamy. Stir in powdered sugar.
Spread frosting over top of cake then sprinkle with toasted coconut. Cut into pieces to serve.

title: onion, arugula and prosciutto focaccia
directions: Mix the flour, oil and salt. Add the yeast mixture and knead with the dough hook attachment of a mixer until smooth. Cover and allow to rest in a warm place for 45 mins.

Preheat the oven to 400°F. Grease and flour a 11 x 15 inch baking pan. Place the proofed dough in the pan and press into the edges to evenly cover the pan. Spread with sour cream then add the onions. Bake for 30-35 mins, until golden brown.
Remove from the oven, top with arugula and prosciutto then cut into 20 squares and serve immediately.

title: banana cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Lightly grease and line an 8 inch cake pan with parchment paper. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, 1 at a time, until combined. Fold in banana and sour cream Sift flour and baking soda together then fold in. Add milk. Transfer to prepared pan and bake for 55-60 mins, until a skewer comes out clean. Let cool for 5 mins in pan before transferring to a wire rack to cool completely.
To make frosting, beat cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth. Spread over cooled cake.

title: chilled sweet rhubarb soup with dumplings
directions: Heat the apple juice, granadine, and 5 tbsp sugar in a large saucepan. Add the rhubarb, cover and simmer for 15-20 mins until the rhubarb is tender.
Stir in the cornstarch paste and simmer for a further minute. Remove from the heat and allow to cool for approximately 1 hour. Transfer to the fridge to chill for 1 hour.

Meanwhile, make the dumplings. Pour the milk into a saucepan with 2 tbsp of sugar, half the orange zest, and the vanilla extract. Bring to a boil. Add 2 tbsp semolina and simmer while stirring for 2-3 mins.
Transfer to a mixing bowl. Allow to cool for 5 mins. Add the egg, then stir in 1 tbsp semolina.
Bring a small pot of water to the boil, add the remaining orange zest and the 1 tbsp of sugar.

Use two teaspoons to scoop 12 small dumplings from the semolina mixture. Place in the boiling water and simmer for 4-5 mins. Remove with a slotted spoon and set aside on a plate lined with paper towels.
Divide the chilled soup between four bowls. Serve with the dumplings and garnish with mint leaves.

title: oat and cranberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Line a 12-cup muffin pan with paper liners.

Combine flour, oats and sugar in a large bowl. Stir in cranberries. Combine milk, lemon juice, oil and egg then stir into flour mixture until just combined. Transfer to prepared pan and bake for 20 mins, or until a skewer inserted in the center comes out clean. Turn out onto a wire rack to cool completely. Serve.

title: salmon and arugula quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Lightly grease a 7 inch fluted tart pan. Line with pie dough, trimming excess. Chill for 10 mins, or until firm.
Meanwhile, blanch arugula in boiling salted water for 20 seconds then shock in ice water. Drain.
Place tart pan on a baking tray. Line with parchment paper and fill with pie weights. Blind bake for 10-12 mins, until pastry is light golden brown.
Reduce oven to 350°F. Arrange salmon, arugula and feta in tart shell. Whisk eggs and cream together, season then pour into tart shell. Bake for 20-25 mins, until just set. Serve warm or cold.

title: pork with cherry sauce
directions: For the cherry sauce, heat half oil and butter together in a frying pan on medium. Saute onion, garlic and Chinese five spice powder 3-4 mins, until tender. Add cherries, orange juice, sugar and vinegar, stirring until sugar dissolves. Simmer 3-4 mins, stirring, until cherries soften slightly. Season to taste.

Meanwhile, heat a large frying pan on high. Brush pork with remaining oil and season to taste. Cook 3-4 mins each side, until cooked as desired. Let rest, covered, 5 mins. Serve with cherry sauce and watercress.

title: crab cakes with spinach
directions: Mix mashed potato with egg yolk and season. Fold in crab meat, tomato and parsley. Shape mixture into 8 patties. Coat in flour, then in beaten egg then in breadcrumbs. Chill 1 hour.
Meanwhile, cook the spinach 1 min in a pan of salted, boiling water, until wilted. Drain
Fry crab cakes in oil, in two batches, 3-4 mins each side until golden. Drain on paper towels and serve hot on a bed of wilted spinach.

title: herb omelette
directions: Mix the eggs, herbs and 1/3 cup water in a large bowl. Beat lightly and season to taste.

Heat a quarter of the butter and 1 teaspoon of the oil in a small frying pan. When the butter is just bubbling, add a quarter of the egg mixture to the pan. Cook over medium heat, tilting the pan, until the egg is just set. Tilt the pan backward, then fold the front half of the omelette over. Cook for 30 seconds, then carefully slide the omelette onto a plate.
Repeat with the remaining butter, oil and egg mixture, wiping out the pan after each omelette.

title: stir-fried curried pork
directions: Prepare curry paste (see below). Mix ground pork and 1 tbsp of the curry paste in a medium bowl.

Heat a wok or large skillet on high heat. Add oil; swirl to coat surface. Add onion; stir-fry for 2 mins. Add ground pork mixture; stir-fry, breaking up lumps, for 5 mins or until browned and cooked through.

Mix cornstarch and 1 cup water. Stir into wok; stir-fry for 3-4 mins or until mixture boils and thickens. Add cabbage; stir-fry for 3 mins or until cabbage wilts. Remove wok from heat. Add sprouts; toss to combine.
Divide lettuce onto serving plates; top with pork mixture. Serve sprinkled with basil and sesame seeds.
For the curry paste, combine all ingredients in a small bowl. Store leftover curry paste, covered, in refrigerator.

title: creamy angel hair pasta
directions: Cook pasta in a large saucepan of boiling salted water according to package directions. Drain, reserving 1 1/2 cups cooking liquid.
Melt butter in same pan on medium heat. Cook bacon 4-5 mins, until crisp. Add capers and lemon peel.
Add pasta, reserved cooking liquid, lemon juice, sun-dried tomatoes, sour cream and spinach leaves. Toss until warmed through. Season to taste. Serve sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.

title: lemon soy chicken
directions: Using kitchen scissors, trim excess skin and fat from chicken pieces. Pat dry with paper towel. Cut drumsticks from thighs. Cut thighs in half.

In a bowl, combine lemon zest, soy sauce, brown sugar and garlic. Brush over chicken and place, skin side up, in a large baking dish. Scatter with lemon slices. Chill, covered, for 3 hours or overnight.

Preheat oven to 350°F. Sprinkle chicken skin with salt. Bake for 40 mins, basting 2-3 times. Transfer to a plate. Increase oven to 400°F. Strain pan juices into small saucepan. Return chicken to baking dish and bake for 10-15 mins, until skin is crisp.

To make gravy, skim excess oil from pan juices with a spoon. Blend cornstarch with a little water, whisk into pan juices. Bring to a boil and simmer for 5-10 mins, until thickened. Serve chicken on a bed of steamed rice with sauce, broccolini and green onions.

title: smoked salmon, egg and rice salad
directions: Cook the rice according to the package instructions. Rinse with cold water. Blanch the peas in boiling water for 30 seconds. Drain.

Mix the honey, mustard, lemon juice and oil. Stir in the chopped dill. Mix the rice, peas, salmon and radicchio. Arrange on 4 serving plates, top with the eggs and drizzle with the dressing. Garnish with the reserved dill.

title: tamarind duck stir-fry
directions: Soak tamarind paste in 1/2 cup boiling water for 30 mins. Pour tamarind into a fine strainer over a small bowl. Push as much pulp through the strainer as possible, scraping underside of strainer occasionally. Discard any tamarind solids left in strainer. Add stock, sauces and sugar to pulp liquid in bowl. Set aside.
Heat oil in wok on high heat. Stir-fry ginger, garlic and chili peppers until fragrant. Add duck and pepper; stir-fry until pepper is tender and duck is heated through.

Add tamarind pulp mixture; bring to a boil. Boil for 1 min. Add bok choy; stir-fry until just wilted. Add snow peas and green onions; stir-fry until both are just tender. Remove wok from heat. Add cilantro leaves and toss gently.

title: berry cheesecake trifles
directions: Divide the sponge cake between eight 1 1/3-cup glasses. Sprinkle with Cointreau and half of the berries.
Sprinkle the gelatin over 1 tbsp water in a small heatproof bowl. Stand the bowl in a small saucepan of simmering water and stir until the gelatin dissolves. Cool for 5 mins.
Beat the cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice in a medium bowl with an electric mixer until smooth. Beat in the cream. Stir in the gelatin mixture.
Divide the mixture between the glasses. Top with the remaining berries. Refrigerate for 15 mins.

For the custard, blend the custard powder, sugar and 1/2 cup of the milk in a small saucepan until smooth. Stir in the remaining milk. Stir on medium heat until the mixture boils and thickens. Remove from the heat. Stir in the butter and egg yolk. Cover the surface of the custard with plastic wrap. Cool.
Divide the custard between the glasses; refrigerate for 30 mins. Garnish with fresh raspberries and blueberries, if desired.

title: green swamp cocktail
directions: Place mint in a chilled highball glass. Combine margarita mix, Midori, tequila and crushed ice in a blender and process for a few seconds. Pour into glass. Slowly add cream on top of drink. Thread olives onto a cocktail skewer and use to garnish drink.
Serve immediately.

title: vegetarian pizza with feta cheese
directions: Sift the flour into a bowl with a pinch of sugar and half a teaspoon of salt. Mix the yeast with 1 cup lukewarm water, and stir into the flour with 3 tablespoons of oil. Knead or use a food processor to mix until the dough is smooth and shiny. Cover the bowl and leave in a warm place for 50 mins.

Meanwhile, put the tomatoes in a bowl and mash them with a fork, then season, adding a pinch of sugar to taste. Add the thyme, keeping aside a tablespoon for decoration. On a floured work surface knead the dough again, then divide into two equal pieces. Roll each piece out into a circle about 10 1/4 inches in diameter, then place each one on a baking sheet lined with baking paper.

To assemble the pizza, spread the tomato mixture over the base, taking care to leave a 1/3 inch border around the edge. Put the vegetables and olives on top and crumble over the feta cheese, then sprinkle with the cayenne pepper. Drizzle over the remaining oil, then bake in the lower half of a preheated oven 425°F. Serve hot with the rest of the thyme sprinkled over the top.

title: broccolini with bacon and eggs
directions: Cook broccolini until tender. Drain.
Meanwhile, melt butter in large frying pan. Cook bacon until crispy. Add bread and garlic. Cook, stirring, until bread is golden brown. Add capers and parsley and toss to combine.
Divide broccolini between serving plates. Top with bacon mixture and eggs.

title: poached turkey with tuna mayonnaise
directions: In a large pot, combine turkey, carrot, celery, onion, parsley and bay leaf. Add enough water to just cover. Bring to a boil, cover and simmer for 30 mins. Remove from heat and let turkey cool in liquid, covered.

Meanwhile, to make the tuna mayonnaise, combine tuna, anchovies, 1 oz capers and 2 tbsp cold turkey cooking liquid in a food processor. Puree until smooth. Mix with mayonnaise and lemon juice. Season.
Thinly slice turkey and arrange on a serving platter. Spoon tuna mayonnaise over top and sprinkle with remaining capers and lemon zest. Garnish with watercress.

title: frozen mojito cocktails
directions: To make the syrup, bring the sugar and 1 cup water to a boil in a saucepan, stirring until the sugar dissolves. Remove from the heat, stir in the whole mint leaves and cool completely. Pour the syrup through a sieve and discard the mint leaves.

Mix the syrup, lemon juice and rum together in a shallow container. Freeze for 3-4 hours, stirring every 30 mins with a fork. Divide between 4 glasses and decorate with the chopped mint and pineapple slices to serve.

title: tuna steaks with pepper and olive salsa
directions: Cook rice in boiling salted water according to package instructions. Drain then mix with butter and season.
For salsa, mix peppers, olives, oregano, lemon juice, sugar and 2 tbsp of oil. Season to taste.
Heat 1-2 tbsp oil in a large non-stick pan and sear tuna for 2-3 mins on each side. Transfer to serving plates, add salsa and serve with rice.

title: apricot and coconut muesli
directions: Combine oats, millet and kamut in a small bowl. Distribute a little muesli between each serving bowl and top with milk, yogurt, apricot and coconut.
Store remaining muesli in an airtight container.

title: pork with vegetables and rice
directions: Cook rice in boiling salted water according to package directions then drain.

Dredge pork belly in cornstarch. Heat oil in a large skillet over high heat, add pork belly and saute, turning often. Remove from pan. Add rice and stir-fry. Add spring onions, garlic and onion and, towards the end, bean sprouts. Add soy sauce then return meat to pan. Season to taste and heat briefly. Serve sprinkled with cashews.

title: smoked fish pie
directions: Place potatoes in a saucepan of salted water. Bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer for 15 mins, or until tender.
Preheat oven to 400°F. Drain potatoes then pass through a ricer or mash well. Add butter and warmed cream and beat until combined. Season to taste.
Beat eggs and remaining cream together. Add nutmeg and lemon zest. Fold in fish, spring onions and dill. Season to taste. Spoon into 4 small pie dishes or ramekins.
Fill a piping bag with hot mashed potatoes. Pipe potatoes on top of pies. Bake for 20 mins, or until golden brown. Serve with lemon wedges and green salad.

title: tofu laksa (spicy noodle soup)
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat, add curry paste and cook for 1 min, or until fragrant. Add coconut milk, 3 cups water and crushed bouillon cube. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 10 mins. Add broccoli, snow peas and tofu and simmer for 3 mins, or until vegetables are tender. Stir in lime juice.
Divide noodles between serving bowls. Ladle hot soup over top. Serve topped with bean sprouts, cilantro and chili.

title: sweet peach and coconut spring rolls
directions: Combine peach, coconut and brown sugar. Place 1 tsp of mixture in the center of each wonton wrapper, brush edges with egg white and roll up. Heat oil in a deep fat fryer or large saucepan and fry spring rolls in batches for 2-3 mins each, until golden brown. Drain on paper towels then arrange on serving plates, drizzle with honey and dust with powdered sugar.

title: easter lamb cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Grease an 8 cup lamb-shaped baking pan and dust with flour. Beat the grated chocolate, butter, sugar and a pinch of salt until creamy. Beat in the eggs one at a time. Sift together the flour, cornstarch and baking powder and fold into the batter.

Spoon batter into the pan and place on a baking sheet. Bake for about 50 mins, until a skewer comes out clean. Allow to cool in the pan for 20 mins, then turn out on to a wire rack and allow to cool completely.

Melt the chopped chocolate in a double boiler. Spread all over the lamb, except the face, reserving a little to draw the face. Sprinkle the lamb with coconut. Draw eyes, nose and mouth with the remaining white chocolate. Allow to dry. Draw pupils with dark chocolate icing. Serve surrounded by chocolate mini eggs.

title: composed seafood lasagna
directions: Bring orange juice, wine, vinegar and saffron to a boil over high heat. Cook for 2-3 mins, until reduced by 1/2. Set aside.
Meanwhile, cook pasta in boiling, salted water according to package instructions. Drain.
Heat oil over high heat and saute zucchini and onion for 2-3 mins, until just tender. Season to taste. Set aside.

Add cream to reduced sauce and return to a simmer over medium heat. Add seafood and poach for 2-3 mins, until just cooked. Transfer seafood to a plate. Gradually whisk cold butter into cream sauce. Season to taste.
Layer pasta on plates with seafood, zucchini mixture and sauce. Top with chives to serve.

title: turkish lamb, mint and spinach
directions: Heat 2 tsp of the oil in wok on high heat. Stir-fry pine nuts until browned. Remove from pan.
Heat 1 tbsp of remaining oil in wok on high heat. Stir-fry lamb, in batches, until browned. Remove from pan.

Heat remaining oil in wok. Stir-fry onion, garlic and chili pepper until onion softens. Add spices; stir-fry until fragrant. Return lamb to wok with pine nuts, spinach and mint; stir-fry until spinach wilts.
Serve pita topped with lamb and combined yogurt and lemon juice.

title: thai green curry shrimp
directions: Heat the oil in a wok or large skillet on high heat. Stir-fry the curry paste for 2-3 mins, until fragrant.
Add the shrimp and stir-fry for 2-3 mins, until they change color. Add the vegetables and stir-fry for 1 min.
Stir in the coconut milk and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to medium and simmer for 2-3 mins, stirring.
Season with lime juice, brown sugar and fish sauce to taste. Serve with rice noodles.

title: spicy chicken and corn bake
directions: Cook the potatoes in boiling water for 20 mins until tender. Drain and set aside to cool.

Preheat the oven to 400°F. Mix together the oil, paprika, cumin and crushed red pepper with a pinch of salt. Rub the mixture onto the chicken drumsticks. Transfer to a large baking dish or 2 smaller ones. Bake for 15 mins.
Meanwhile, wrap the potatoes in the bacon. Add them, along with the pepper strips, corn, shallots, and jalapeno to the chicken and cook for an additional 20-25 mins.

title: apple brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Toss the chopped apples in lemon juice and set aside. Melt the butter and 10 oz chocolate in a small saucepan over low heat, stirring. Remove from the heat and allow to cool 5-10 mins. Pour the cooled chocolate into a large mixing bowl, add the sugar, vanilla sugar, 1 pinch salt, eggs, 1 3/4 cups walnuts, flour and baking powder. Beat until mixture is smooth, then pour into a greased cake pan.
Distribute apples evenly on top of the mixture. Sprinkle with remaining walnuts. Bake for 40-45 mins. Then allow to cool for 2-3 hours on a wire rack.
To decorate, melt the remaining chocolate with the coconut oil and cream over low heat, stirring. Allow to cool for 15 mins, then drizzle over the cake. Leave for 2 hours to set.

title: onion soup with cheese croutons
directions: Heat the oil in a large pan and saute the onions for 10 mins until soft, adding the sugar after 5 mins. Sprinkle with flour and cook for 1 min then gradually stir in the stock and wine. Bring to a boil then reduce the heat and simmer for 8 mins. Stir in most of the parsley and season to taste with salt and freshly ground black pepper.
Toast the bread under the broiler. Cut four circles from each slice of toast and top with the grated cheese. Broil until the cheese has melted.
Serve the soup in warmed bowls topped with the cheese toasts and sprinkled with the rest of the parsley.

title: beef and mushroom lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F. Lightly grease a medium baking dish. For the red sauce, heat oil in a large frying pan on high and saute onion and garlic 4-5 mins, until tender. Add beef and cook 4-5 mins, until browned, breaking up clumps with a spoon. Add mushrooms and cook, stirring, 2-3 mins. Stir in tomato paste, tomatoes and wine. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 8-10 mins, until thickened. Add parsley and season to taste.

Meanwhile, for the white sauce, melt butter in a medium saucepan on high. Add flour and cook, stirring, 1 min. Remove from heat. Stir in milk. Return to heat and cook, stirring, until sauce boils and thickens. Simmer 3 mins. Stir in ricotta and season to taste.
Place 1 layer of lasagna sheets in prepared dish. Spoon 1/2 red sauce and 1/2 white sauce on top. Sprinkle with 1/4 of the cheese. Repeat, finishing with lasagna sheets.
Whisk cream and egg together in a small bowl. Pour on top of final lasagna sheet layer. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake 30-35 mins, until golden. Cool 5 mins before serving.

title: potato cakes
directions: Sift the flour and baking powder together. Stir in the mashed potato, butter and chives. Season to taste. Using wet hands, shape dough into a ball and then flatten the ball into a disc about 7 inches across. Cut into 8 wedges.
Melt a little butter in a frying pan or griddle pan. Cook the potato cakes for about 4 mins on each side. Serve with grilled tomatoes and fried mushrooms.

title: curry chicken rissoles
directions: Combine finely grated onion, ground chicken, squash, mint, breadcrumbs, peas and curry paste. Shape into 24 rissoles, each using around 2 tbsp mixture. Lightly coat in chickpea flour then cover and chill for 15 mins.
For the salsa, combine remaining onion, tomatoes, cilantro and lemon juice. Cover with plastic wrap and chill.
Heat oil in a large nonstick frying pan over medium-low heat. Cook rissoles, in batches, for 2-3 mins per side, or until browned and cooked through.
Arrange pappadums on serving plates. Top each with rice, cucumbers, a rissole, yogurt and salsa. Serve with remaining salsa.

title: marbled bundt cake with poppy seeds
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Melt the dark chocolate in a heat proof bowl over simmering water, remove from the heat. Beat the butter, sugar and vanilla extract until creamy. Gradually stir in the eggs. Sift the flour with the baking powder. Alternate adding the milk and flour in 3 batches to the butter mixture, stirring well after each addition. Divide the cake mixture into 3. Stir the ground poppy seeds into one third, the almond paste into another and the chocolate into the last third.

Grease and flour a 9 inch diameter Bundt pan and fill it first with the poppy seed mixture, followed by the almond paste and chocolate mixtures at the same time to fill the pan. Bake the cake for 55-65 mins.
Take the cake out of the oven and let it rest for about 10 mins in the pan. Turn it out onto a wire rack and let it cool down.

Melt the white chocolate in a heat proof bowl over simmering water and mix it with the coconut oil. Let it cool slightly and spread it over the cake. Sprinkle it with poppy seeds and leave the chocolate to set before serving.

title: vegetable and chickpea fritters
directions: Combine chickpea flour, vegetables, garlic, spices, baking powder and 1/4 cup water in a medium bowl. Mix in cilantro then shape into 16 fritters.
Working in batches, shallow-fry fritters until browned and cooked through. Drain on paper towels and season.
Serve fritters with yogurt.

title: healthy cottage cheese burgers
directions: Mix the ground beef, cottage cheese, egg, onion, bell pepper, parsley, breadcrumbs and 1 tbsp mustard in a bowl. Season with salt and pepper to taste, mix well and shape into 4 thin burgers.
Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the burgers and cook for 2 mins per side. Reduce heat to medium and cook for another 4-5 mins per side for medium doneness.

Mix the mayonnaise with the remaining 1/2 tbsp mustard. Spread evenly over the roll bottoms. Top with the lettuce, tomato and cucumber slices. Add a burger, some ketchup, then more lettuce, tomato and cucumber. Sandwich with the roll tops and serve.

title: spiced spinach pilaf with chicken
directions: For the pilaf, heat oil in a large saucepan on medium and saute onion 3-4 mins, until tender. Add coriander, cinnamon, cumin, chili flakes and turmeric. Cook 1 min, stirring, until fragrant. Add rice and cook, stirring, 1 min. Stir in chicken stock and tomatoes. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer, covered, 15 mins, or until rice is just tender. Remove from heat and cool 5 mins.
Meanwhile, preheat grill on high. Brush chicken with oil and grill 4-5 mins on each side, until cooked through. Cut each piece in half.
To finish, stir spinach into rice mixture. Season to taste and top with chicken to serve.

title: chocolate orange dessert muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Grease 12-cup muffin pan.

Sift flour, cocoa powder and sugar into large bowl. Stir in butter, buttermilk, egg, liqueur and orange peel. Spoon into prepared pan. Break each chocolate into 3 or 4 pieces. Push chocolates into muffin, make sure that chocolate does not touch sides of muffin pan and that batter almost covers the chocolate.
Bake about 20 mins. Cool in pan 5 mins. Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack.

For the custard sauce, beat egg yolks and sugar in medium bowl with an electric mixer until thick and pale. Bring milk just to a boil in a small saucepan. Whisk hot milk into yolk mixture. Return mixture to pan. Stir on medium-low heat, without boiling, until mixture thickens and coats back of spoon.
Garnish muffins with orange sections, if desired. Serve with custard sauce.

title: seven hours lamb
directions: Preheat the oven to 250°F. Mix the white wine, brandy, tomato puree and 1 cup of water. Peel 10 garlic cloves and cut them in half lengthways. Pierce the lamb 20 times with a small, sharp knife and press a piece of garlic into each hole. Press a little butter into each hole and and spread the oil all over the lamb. Put the lamb in a roasting pan and arrange the carrots and onions around it. Pour in the wine and brandy mixture and cook for 7 hours, basting occasionally and adding some water from time to time.
Cut 2 heads of garlic in half crosswise and brush each half with oil. Put the garlic together again, wrap it in aluminium foil and cook it for about 3 hours with the leg of lamb.
Remove the lamb and garlic from the oven, put them on a plate and put them back in the switched-off oven to keep warm.

Pour the meat juices and vegetables into a pot with 1 cup of water and puree the mixture. Top it off with about 4 cups with water, bring to the boil, thicken it with cornstarch, add the sugar and season to taste.

Cook the frozen beans in boiling salted water for about 5 minutes, then drain them in a colander. Put them back in the pot with 2 oz of butter and them gently. Serve the lamb on a platter with a little sauce, the garlic halves and the beans, with some bread on the side.

title: zucchini and bacon quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Lightly grease a 9 inch pie dish. Sprinkle with 1 tbsp breadcrumbs.

Heat olive oil in a medium frying pan over high heat. Saute bacon for 4-5 mins, until crispy. Add garlic and cook, stirring, for 1 min. Transfer to a large bowl and let cool slightly. Add zucchini, eggs, cheese, heavy cream and flour. Season. Transfer to prepared pan and sprinkle with remaining breadcrumbs. Bake for 25-30 mins, until just set. Let stand for 10 mins before serving.

title: mediterranean polenta tart
