In a blender, combine walnuts and enough hot braising meat to make a smooth sauce. Blend in thyme and season to taste. Set aside.
Melt butter in a clean frying pan. Saute asparagus to heat through. Slice meat and place on warmed serving plates along with asparagus. Spoon sauce over top and sprinkle with extra nuts.

title: chocolate and strawberry tartlets
directions: Sift the flour, cocoa and baking powder into a mixing bowl. Add the sugar, vanilla extract, egg, butter and a pinch of salt and knead to a smooth dough. Wrap in foil and refrigerate for 30 mins.

Preheat the oven to 400°F. Grease a 12-hole cupcake pan. On a floured surface, roll out the dough to about 1/8 inch thick. Using a 3 1/2 inch diameter pastry cutter, cut out 12 circles and lay in the pan, pressing the edges down. Bake for 15 mins. Allow to cool in the pan for 5 mins, then carefully transfer to a wire rack and allow to cool completely.

In a saucepan, bring the cream to a boil, then remove from the heat. Add the chocolate and stir until melted. Allow to cool at room temperature for 30 mins, stirring occasionally. Spoon into the tartlet crusts and chill for at least 1 hour.

Place a whole strawberry in the middle of each tartlet and arrange the halved strawberries around the edge. Heat the jam until smooth and brush over the strawberries. Allow to cool, then decorate with mint leaves.

title: linguine with lemon crumbs
directions: Cook pasta in boiling salted water until al dente. Drain.
Meanwhile, heat lemon-infused olive oil in a frying pan over medium-high heat. Cook breadcrumbs for 7 mins, or until crisp and golden. Season.

Combine garlic, olive oil, tomatoes and basil in a mixing bowl. Add pasta and toss to combine. Season. Distribute between serving bowls and top with lemon breadcrumbs. Sprinkle with Parmesan to serve.

title: chicken tortilla wraps with roquefort cheese
directions: To hard boil the eggs, place eggs in a saucepan and cover with water. Bring water to a boil over medium heat. Once the water reaches a boil, remove from the heat. Let eggs sit in hot water for 12 minutes, drain then run under cold water. Peel. Chop 1 egg into small cubes, thinly slice remaining 2 eggs.
Meanwhile, heat oil in a frying pan. Season chicken then saute for about 10 mins, turning. Remove from pan, allow to cool slightly then cut into thin strips.

Mix chopped anchovies with blue cheese, cream cheese and cubed egg to create a paste, then season. Warm tortillas in oven or microwave then lay out and spread with anchovy paste. Add a layer of chicken, remaining anchovies, lettuce and sliced egg. Roll up tortillas then wrap each in foil and chill. To serve, remove foil and cut each tortilla into 3.

title: coconut truffles
directions: Combine coconut cream, lemon peel and chocolate in small saucepan. Stir on low heat until smooth. Transfer mixture to medium bowl. Cover; refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Working with a quarter of the chocolate mixture at a time (keeping remaining in the refrigerator), roll rounded teaspoons into balls; place on tray. Refrigerate truffles until firm.
Working quickly, roll truffles in coconut. Return to tray. Refrigerate until firm.

title: linguine with fried feta, arugula and cherry tomatoes
directions: In a bowl, beat the egg and season with black pepper. Place the breadcrumbs in a second bowl. Roll the feta in the egg, then the breadcrumbs.

Heat 6 tbsp oil in a large skillet or frying pan. Add the arugula and deep fry for 30 seconds. Lift out with a slotted spoon and drain on kitchen towels. Clean the pan and heat 4 tbsp oil in it. Fry the feta until crispy all over, then remove and drain on paper towels.

Clean the pan again and heat 3 tbsp oil. Saute the mushrooms over a high heat, turning, until browned. Remove from the pan. Add 2 tbsp oil to the pan and fry the tomatoes for 3 mins, turning. Meanwhile, cook the pasta in boiling salted water according to the pack instructions. Drain, reserving the water.
Add the mushrooms and sugar to the tomatoes and cook until just caramelized. Season with salt and black pepper. Add the vinegar and 2/3 cup of the pasta water. Simmer for 1 min.
Toss together the pasta, tomatoes and feta. Divide between 4 serving plates and sprinkle over the arugula.

title: molten caramel cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease 4 - 8.5 oz ramekins.
Combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar and a pinch of salt. Add milk, egg, vanilla and butter. Whisk until smooth.

Divide honey between ramekins. Distribute batter over top. Sprinkle each with 1 tbsp brown sugar then gently pour 1/4 cup boiling water into each ramekin. Bake for 20-25 mins, or until puffed and golden. Serve immediately with ice cream.

title: spicy butterflied chicken
directions: Mix the oil, lime juice, oregano, red pepper flakes, paprika and garlic in a baking dish. Add the chicken, turning to coat in the marinade. Cover and refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight.
Preheat the oven to 350°F. Place the chickens on a wire rack set over a roasting pan. Pour any marinade over the top.
Roast for 45-50 mins or until golden and cooked through. Garnish with whole oregano leaves, if desired.

title: lemon polenta cake with lemon compote
directions: Preheat the oven to 300°F. For the lemon compote, thinly slice the lemons then cut the slices into quarters; remove the seeds. Layer the lemon pieces in a medium baking dish. Place the sugar, rosemary and 1 cup water in a small saucepan on low heat. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Bring to a boil on high heat. Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, for 1 min. Pour the syrup over the lemons. Cover with parchment paper then seal the dish with foil. Bake for 30 mins. Remove the foil and paper. Bake for a further 30 mins or until the syrup is thick and the lemons are caramelized. Set aside.
Preheat the oven to 350°F. For the lemon polenta cake, grease an 8-inch round cake pan. Line bottom and side with parchment paper.

Beat the butter and sugar in a large bowl with an electric mixer until pale and creamy. Beat in the eggs, one at a time, beating until combined between additions. Stir in the ground almonds, cornmeal and baking powder. Stir in the lemon peel and juice and orange flower water. Spread in the prepared pan; smooth the surface.
Bake for about 1 hour or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool cake in pan on wire rack.
Serve cake with lemon compote and heavy cream, if desired.

title: bolognese cannelloni
directions: Heat 1 tbsp oil in a medium saucepan. Cook celery, onion, carrot, chilies and garlic, stirring, until onion softens. Add pancetta and cook, stirring, for 3 mins. Remove from pan.

Add remaining oil to pan. Cook beef and pork, stirring, until browned. Return pancetta mixture to pan along with wine. Bring to a boil and cook, uncovered, until reduced by 1/2. Add milk and bring to a boil. Boil, uncovered, until reduced by 1/2. Add stock, tomatoes and tomato paste. Bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for about 1 hour 10 mins, or until thickened. Season. Let cool for 20 mins.
Preheat oven to 400°F. Oil a large shallow baking dish. Combine cream and cheese in large measuring cup. Season. Spread 1 cup of cream mixture over base of prepared dish.

Arrange cannelloni pieces on a clean work surface. Place 1/4 cup beef mixture along 1 short side of each piece then roll up to enclose. Place cannelloni, seam-side down, in prepared dish. Pour remaining cream mixture over top then cover dish with foil. Bake for 30 mins. Uncover and bake about 15 mins, or until browned. Let stand for 5 mins before serving.

title: char grilled beef salad
directions: Combine beef with 2 tbsp fish sauce and 1 tbsp lime juice. Cover and chill for 3 hours, or overnight.
Drain beef. Cook on a heated, oiled grill plate (or grill) until browned and cooked to your liking. Cover beef and let rest for 5 mins. Slice thinly.

Meanwhile, combine cucumber, chilies, onions, tomatoes and herbs in a large bowl. Combine remaining fish sauce and lime juice with sugar, soy sauce and garlic and whisk to combine. Pour over salad. Add beef and toss to combine.

title: pappardelle marinara
directions: To make the Napoletana sauce, heat olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Sweat onion, stirring, until soft. Stir in garlic and cook for 1 min. Add tomato paste and tomatoes. Cook, stirring, for 1 min. Add wine and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 3 mins. Season.
Add seafood mix and saffron to pan. Bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer for 5 mins, or until seafood is cooked through.
Meanwhile, cook pasta in boiling salted water until tender. Drain.
Add pasta to sauce and toss to combine. Serve with basil and Parmesan sprinkled on top.

title: watercress, apple and blue cheese salad
directions: Heat a medium frying pan over high heat. Cook prosciutto for 2-3 mins, until golden and crisp. Drain on paper towels.
In a large bowl, combine watercress, apples, blue cheese, almonds and prosciutto. Set aside.
To make the cider vinaigrette, whisk together olive oil, cider vinegar, lemon juice, garlic and sugar. Season to taste. Drizzle over salad just before serving. Serve with crusty bread.

title: tuna sashimi
directions: Soak daikon in ice water for 15 mins then drain.
Arrange tuna slices between 4 serving plates. Place daikon next to tuna. Garnish plates with wasabi and pickled ginger. Serve with a separate bowl of soy sauce.

title: vodka and cranberry cooler
directions: Place the vodka, triple sec, liqueur and cranberry juice in an ice-filled glass.
Add apple slices and berries. Serve.

title: chunky beef, bean and broccoli soup
directions: Heat the oil in a large saucepan on high heat. Add beef and cook, stirring, 2-3 mins or until browned. Remove from pan.

Add onion and bacon to the pan and saute 2-3 mins. Add garlic and saute 1 min. Return beef to the pan. Add stock, tomatoes and oregano and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 1 hour or until beef is tender.
Add broccoli and beans to the pan. Simmer 4-5 mins or until broccoli is tender. Season to taste. Sprinkle with basil and Parmesan cheese.

title: beet carpaccio with potato croquettes
directions: For the marinated beets, whisk the vinegar and olive oil with 1 tbsp honey and season. Add the shallot and beet and set aside.
Cook the potatoes in boiling salted water for 20 mins. Drain and press through a potato ricer. Add the potato starch and egg yolks and season with salt and nutmeg. Allow to cool.

Meanwhile, beat the whole eggs in a deep dish and place the flour and breadcrumbs on separate plates. Form the potato mixture into small balls and roll in the flour, then dip in the egg, then roll in the breadcrumbs. Heat the vegetable oil in a large saucepan or deep fat fryer and fry the potato balls until golden and crispy. Remove with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.
Arrange the sliced beet on plates and top with the potato croquettes. Mix the creme fraiche and 1 tbsp honey and season then drizzle over the beet carpaccio and croquettes and garnish with basil.

title: zucchini and peanut burgers
directions: In a large bowl, combine zucchini, peanuts, eggs, parsley, rice and breadcrumbs. Shape into 6 patties.
Toss patties in flour, shaking off excess. Heat oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. Cook patties for 3-4 mins, or until browned.

title: fresh pasta dough
directions: Combine flour and 1/2 tsp salt in a food processor. With motor running, add eggs, 1 at a time. Process until dough is elastic and firm, about 2 mins. Turn dough out onto a floured surface and knead lightly. Wrap in plastic wrap and let rest for 30 mins.
On a lightly floured work surface, cut dough in 1/2 then roll out each section to 1/8 inch thick. Dust with flour then fold in 1/2 and cut into 1/4 inch wide strips.
Cook pasta in boiling, salted water for about 2-3 mins, until al dente. Drain and toss with olive oil, Parmesan and herbs. Serve.

title: curried sausages with sweet potato and cauliflower purée
directions: Steam sweet potatoes for 10 mins. Add cauliflower and steam for another 8 mins, or until tender.

Meanwhile, heat 1/2 tbsp oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. Add sausages and cook for 8 mins, or until browned. Set aside. Add remaining oil. Saute onion for 4 mins, or until soft. Add curry paste and flour. Cook for 1 min. Gradually whisk in 1 2/3 cups water. Bring to a boil. Return sausages to pan along with peas. Cook, covered, over medium heat for 4 mins, or until sausages are cooked through.
Drain sweet potatoes and cauliflower. Return to pan along with butter and milk. Using a stick blender, puree until smooth.
Serve sausages with sweet potato and cauliflower puree.

title: coffee hazelnut shots
directions: Place hazelnut liqueur, 1/4 cup water, instant coffee granules and brown sugar in a small saucepan on low heat. Stir until sugar dissolves. Simmer for about 5 mins or until syrup thickens slightly.
Divide hazelnut gelato among 4 serving glasses. Pour coffee syrup over gelato. Serve sprinkled with the hazelnuts.

title: sun dried tomato dip with lavash chips
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Line 2 baking trays with parchment paper.
Lightly coat lavash in olive oil. Season. Transfer to prepared trays and bake for 5-10 mins, until golden brown and crisp. Let cool.

Meanwhile, place sun-dried tomatoes in a food processor. Pulse until roughly chopped. Add cream cheese and milk and process until smooth. Transfer to a serving bowl and stir in chives. Season. Serve with lavash chips.

title: grilled polenta crostini
directions: Preheat grill. In a bowl, marinate onion in vinegar. In a separate bowl, combine pepper, garlic, basil and 1 tbsp olive oil.

Slice polenta into 1/2 inch thick rounds. Brush with remaining oil. Grill for 4 mins, turning once, or until lightly browned. Cut polenta slices in 1/2. Top with pepper mixture and drained onions. Serve warm, at room temperature or cold.

title: tomatoes stuffed with buttery rice pilaf and chermoula
directions: To make the chermoula, place herbs, garlic, lemon juice, spices and salt in a food processor and process until smooth. With the machine running, gradually add oil. Transfer to a bowl and adjust seasoning, if necessary. Cover and refrigerate until required.

To make the pilaf, melt butter in a medium saucepan over medium heat. Sweat onion until tender. Add rice, cumin seeds and raisins. Pour in stock. Bring to a gentle boil then reduce heat to low, cover pan and cook for 12 mins. Remove pan from heat. Let stand, covered, for 5 mins. Season.
Preheat oven to 450°F.

Arrange tomatoes upside down on a plate for 10 mins to drain. Sprinkle insides with coriander seeds and season. Fill with rice, pressing firmly into tomatoes. Transfer to a shallow baking dish lined with baking paper. Place reserved tomato tops, cut-side down, in prepared dish and season. Sprinkle cheese over top then breadcrumbs. Bake for 15 mins, or until cheese is golden. Let cool slightly. Serve with chermoula.

title: fresh pasta
directions: Sift flour and salt into a large bowl. Make a well in the center. Break eggs into well then gradually mix flour into eggs. Press mixture into a ball and transfer to a floured work surface and knead for 10 mins, or until smooth and elastic.

Cut dough in 1/2. Roll each portion through a pasta machine on the thickest setting. Fold dough in 1/2 then roll through machine again. Repeat folding and rolling, adjusting setting on machine to become thinner with each roll. Dust dough with a little extra flour when necessary. Roll until 1mm thick, or to desired thickness. Cut into desired pasta shape.

title: best ever bolognese sauce
directions: Heat the oil in a 6-quart pressure cooker. Cook the onion and garlic, stirring, until the onion softens. Add the ground meat; cook, stirring, until browned. Add the tomato paste, undrained tomatoes and wine to the cooker and secure the lid. Bring the cooker up to high pressure. Reduce the heat to stabilize the pressure, if required and cook for 20 mins.
Release the pressure using the quick release method and remove the lid. Simmer, uncovered, for about 10 mins or until the sauce slightly thickens. Stir in the herbs and season to taste.

title: pineapple with pistachio praline
directions: Lightly coat a baking tray with oil. Scatter nuts over tray. Gently heat sugar and 2 tbsp water until melted. Bring to a boil and cook, without stirring, for 6 mins, or until golden brown. Carefully pour over nuts. Tilt tray to spread out thinly. Set aside to cool. Break into pieces then chop.
Arrange pineapple slices on serving plates. Drizzle with rum. Sprinkle with praline.

title: egg and cheese tostada
directions: To make tortillas, mix cornmeal and flour with a pinch of salt. Gradually add 1/2 cup water and knead with the dough hook of a mixer then with your hands into a smooth, firm dough. Cover and let rest for about 1 hour.
For sauce, heat 1 tbsp oil in a frying pan and sweat onions, garlic and chili for about 3 mins, until soft, then add tomato paste. Set aside.

Preheat oven to 325°F. Divide dough into 8 equal-sized balls and roll out on a floured surface into 6 inch discs. Working in batches, heat remaining oil in a frying pan and cook dough for about 1 min per side. Spread tomato and chili paste evenly over each tortilla and transfer to an oiled baking sheet. Break an egg onto each tortilla, sprinkle with cheese and bake for about 17 mins. Sprinkle with parsley to serve.

title: vegetable cannelloni baked in bechamel sauce
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Lightly grease a deep 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

Heat the oil in a medium saucepan on high heat. Saute the onion and garlic for 2-3 mins. Add the vegetables and cook for 2-3 mins. Remove from the heat and stir in the ricotta cheese and 1/3 cup of the Parmesan cheese. Season to taste and cool.

Spread 1/2 the tomato puree in the bottom of the prepared dish. Spoon the ricotta mixture into a piping bag fitted with a large plain tip. Pipe into the cannelloni tubes. Arrange the cannelloni in a single layer in the dish. Pour the remaining tomato puree over the top.

For the bechamel sauce, melt the butter in a medium saucepan on medium heat. Add the flour and cook for 1 min, stirring. Pour in the milk. Bring to a boil, whisking to remove any lumps. Simmer for 3 mins. Pour the sauce over the cannelloni. Sprinkle with the remaining 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese and nutmeg.
Bake for 30-35 mins, until golden. Serve topped with arugula leaves.

title: crispy pizza with caramelized onions, anchovies, tomatoes and olives
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water with 1 tsp sugar. Set aside for 5 mins, until frothy.

Meanwhile. sift flour and 1 tsp salt into a large bowl. Make a well in the center and add yeast mixture and olive oil. Mix until combined then knead on a lightly floured surface until smooth. Place in a greased bowl, cover and set aside in a warm place for about 1 hour, or until doubled in size.
Meanwhile, heat reserved anchovy oil in a large frying pan over low heat. Cook onions for 15-20 mins, until soft. Add balsamic vinegar and brown sugar. Cook for 10 mins.

Preheat oven to 400°F. Lightly grease 2 - 12 inch pizza pans. Knead dough until smooth. Cut in half then roll out and press onto pizza pans. Spread onion mixture over dough and arrange tomatoes, olives and anchovies over top. Sprinkle with rosemary. Bake for 10-15 mins, until golden brown. Serve in wedges.

title: chicken soup with julienne vegetables
directions: Place the chicken, bay leaf, cloves, juniper berries, onions and 2 quarts water in a saucepan and simmer for 30 mins, skimming occasionally. Add the halved carrot, celeriac and leeks and simmer for 30 mins, skimming occasionally.

Cook the pasta in boiling salted water for 5 mins. Drain and set aside. Pour the soup through a sieve into a clean saucepan. Remove the chicken and discard the skin and bones. Slice the meat. Bring the soup to a boil, add the carrot, celeriac and leek strips and simmer for 3 mins. Season with salt. Add the chicken and pasta and warm through.

title: affogato
directions: Place ice cream in serving bowls and decorate with wafers. Serve with espresso and Irish cream liqueur for guests to pour over the ice cream themselves.

title: sicilian chard
directions: Cover raisins in boiling water and soak for 30 mins. Drain and return to the bowl; add the vinegar. Process panko in a blender or food processor until crumbs are finer. Mix with Parmesan cheese and 1/2 tsp salt in a shallow dish.

Place the flour in a clean plastic bag. Add chard stems (the stems need to be wet for the flour to stick). Toss until the stems are coated in flour. Brush stems with beaten egg then coat in the Parmesan crumbs. Place the stems on a wire rack as they are coated.
Add chard leaves to a saucepan of salted, gently boiling water; cook for 5 mins. Drain; rinse with cold water and drain. Squeeze excess water, then chop finely.

Heat 1/2 tbsp of the extra virgin olive oil in a large skillet. Add pine nuts and cook gently, stirring often, until golden. Remove with a slotted spoon and drain on parchment paper. Sprinkle with sea salt.

Wipe skillet clean. Heat 1 tbsp extra virgin olive oil in skillet on low heat. Add chili pepper and raisins. Cook for 1 min. Add chopped chard leaves and 1/4 tsp salt. Toss gently. Transfer to a heated bowl.
Wipe skillet clean. Heat 1/2 cup olive oil on medium heat. Cook chard stems in batches until golden all over. Transfer to wire rack.
Drizzle chard leaves with remaining 1 tbsp extra virgin olive oil and sprinkle with pine nuts. Place chard stems on a platter. Sprinkle with sea salt. Serve with lemon wedges.

title: baked fennel with pork medallions
directions: Place lemon and fennel in a pot of boiling, salted water and simmer for 7-9 mins until just tender. Remove and rinse under cold water. Set aside.
For Parmesan breadcrumbs, mix 1/2 the onions and 1/2 the garlic with 3 tbsp olive oil, breadcrumbs, and Parmesan. Set aside.

Preheat oven to 350°F. Heat 1 tbsp oil, saute remaining onion and garlic for 3-4 mins then add chopped tomatoes and vinegar. Bring to a boil, season and add sugar. Transfer to a baking dish. Press Parmesan breadcrumbs into fennel pieces then arrange in the baking dish. Bake for 25-30 mins.

Meanwhile, roll pork in mustard then wrap a piece of bacon around each and secure using toothpicks. Heat remaining oil in a frying pan and sear the pork for 8-10 mins, turning. Serve with baked fennel and sauce.

title: couscous and carrot patties with sesame salad
directions: Prepare couscous according to package instructions then let cool. Once cool, combine with carrot, ricotta, egg and curry powder and season. Divide into 16 patties. Heat oil in a nonstick frying pan and fry patties, turning, until golden brown, working in batches if necessary.
Meanwhile, mix vinegar with sesame oil and 1-2 tbsp canola oil and season. Toss with cilantro, chili, onion and cucumber. Serve patties on a plate with salad on the side.

title: shrimp linguine with chili butter sauce
directions: Cook pasta in a large saucepan of boiling salted water according to package directions. Drain well.
Meanwhile, heat oil in a large deep skillet on high heat. Add shrimp; cook and turn, 2-3 mins, or until shrimp just change color. Transfer to a plate. Cover with foil to keep warm.
Add garlic and chili pepper to pan, cook and stir, 1 min. Add wine and lemon juice; bring to a boil. Boil until liquid reduces by half.
Reduce heat to low. Add butter, 1 piece at a time, whisking constantly until sauce is smooth and thickened slightly.
Add cream, stir to combine. Return shrimp to pan. Add chives and pasta, toss 1 min, or until heated through.

title: rustic tomato pizzas
directions: To make the dough, sift the flour into a bowl with the salt, then mix in the olive oil and dissolved yeast. Using either a food processor with a dough hook or your hands, mix to create a smooth dough. Place in a bowl, cover and leave to rise in a warm place for 30 mins.

Knead the dough again for a few minutes, then divide it into four equal pieces. On a floured work surface, roll each piece out into a rough oval shape, then transfer to 2 lined baking sheets. Loosely cover and leave to rise in warm place for about 15 mins. Preheat the oven to 400°F.

Mix the tomato sauce with the chopped basil and season to taste. Spread on the dough and top with the tomatoes and mozzarella. Bake for 25-30 mins. Garnish with the remaining basil leaves and serve hot

title: tomato and bean soup
directions: Preheat broiler on high. Line broiler with foil.

Heat olive oil in a large saucepan on high heat. Saute onion and garlic 1-2 mins until onion is tender. Stir in stock, tomatoes and seasoning mix. Simmer 5 min. (Puree tomato mixture, if desired). Stir in beans and season to taste. Simmer 5 mins.
Meanwhile, arrange bread slices on prepared pan. Broil until toasted on one side. Turn and sprinkle each evenly with cheese.
Broil 1-2 mins until cheese melts. Serve soup sprinkled with chives or parsley. Accompany with cheese toast.

title: coconut ricotta pancakes with tropical fruit salsa
directions: For the salsa, combine fruit in a medium bowl. Place mint, lime juice, brown sugar and ginger in a mortar and pestle and pound to form a paste. Spoon over fruit, tossing to combine.
For the pancakes, sift flour and baking powder into a large bowl. Stir in sugar. Whisk coconut milk, ricotta, egg and vanilla in a medium bowl. Stir into dry ingredients until combined.

Heat a large non-stick skillet on medium heat. Brush with a little melted butter. Drop heaping tablespoons of batter into pan. Cook for 3-4 mins until bubbles form and break on top. Turn and cook for 1 min, until golden. Remove from pan. Keep warm while cooking remaining pancakes.
Serve pancakes topped with fruit salsa, toasted coconut and a dollop of yogurt.

title: fish tartare in avocado shells
directions: Juice 3 of the lime halves. Cut remaining half into slices. In a small bowl, combine the diced fish and half the lime juice. Place in refrigerator for 15 minutes.

Without damaging the skin, carefully remove pulp from avocados and dice about 1/2 inch. Fold the diced pulp and shallots into the chilled tartare. Drizzle oil over tartare and season with salt, pepper, paprika, and remaining lime juice. Return tartare to refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Fold half of chopped dill into tartare. Fill avocado shells with tartare and garnish with salmon caviar, remaining dill, and lime slices. Serve immediately.

title: brownie bombs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease and line a deep 7 1/4 inch square cake pan with parchment paper.

Stir butter and semisweet chocolate over low heat until smooth. Transfer to a medium bowl and let cool. Add sugar, egg and flour and mix until combined. Transfer to prepared pan and bake for 20 mins. Let cool in pan.

Cut cake into large pieces. Using a food processor, process cake and rum until mixture just comes together. Shape rounded teaspoons of mixture into balls. Place on a baking tray lined with parchment paper. Freeze for 1 hour or chill for 3 hours or overnight, until firm.
Dip the end of 1 lollipop stick into melted chocolate then push about halfway into a cake pop. Return to tray. Repeat with remaining sticks and cake pops. Freeze for about 5 mins to set.

Coat cake pops in chocolate, allowing excess to drain off. Place on a baking tray lined with parchment paper. Sprinkle with pearls before chocolate sets. Let stand at room temperature until set. Serve in paper liners.

title: banana pancakes with pistachios and ice cream
directions: Place the pistachios in a food processor. Pulse until fine crumbs. Set aside.
Sift the flour into a large bowl. Add the brown sugar, buttermilk and eggs and mix until combined and smooth.

Heat a small nonstick skillet on medium heat. Brush with a little butter. For each pancake, pour 1/4 cup of batter into the pan. Spread to a 4 1/2-inch round. Cook for 1 min. Place 4-5 slices of banana on top and cook for a further 1 min, until bubbles appear on the surface. Turn and cook for 2-3 mins until golden brown and cooked through. Transfer to a plate. Cover with foil to keep warm. Repeat with the remaining butter and batter to make 12 pancakes.
Stack 2 pancakes on each serving plate. Top with small scoops of ice cream. Serve sprinkled with the pistachio crumbs and drizzled with maple syrup.

title: baked sweet potatoes with tuna, onions and sour cream
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Cut the sweet potatoes in half lengthwise. Place on a foil-lined baking pan. Drizzle with 1-2 tbsp of the oil and season to taste. Bake for 30-40 mins, until tender.
Mix the tuna, onion, cilantro, chili pepper, lemon juice and remaining 2 tbsp oil in a large bowl. Season to taste.
Place potato halves on 4 plates. Top each with tuna salad and a dollop of sour cream. Serve sprinkled with black pepper and garnished with cilantro leaves.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Combine bread, sausage, bacon, peppers and tomatoes in a baking pan, drizzle with oil and salt and pepper and toss to coat.
Bake for 15-20 mins, turning once, until bread is golden and tomatoes are tender. Sprinkle with parsley and chives. Serve with poached eggs if desired.

title: chargrilled zucchini blossoms stuffed with chili and mint ricotta
directions: Combine cheese, mint, lemon zest, chili flakes, garlic and egg yolk in a medium bowl. Season to taste. Stuff zucchini blossoms with mixture, leaving a 1/2 inch gap at the top. Twist petal tops to enclose filling.
Brush blossoms with oil. Cook on a heated grill plate (or grill) over high heat for 1 min per side, or until lightly charred and heated through. Season to taste. Serve with lemon slices.

title: pear-date crumble with honey-oat topping
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease a shallow baking dish.
Combine pears, 1/4 cup water and lemon zest. Cook, uncovered, for about 10 mins, or until just tender. Discard lemon zest and add dates. Transfer to prepared dish.
Combine flour and oats. Cut in reduced-fat spread. Add honey and spices. Sprinkle over top of pears. Bake for 30 mins, until lightly browned.

title: aromatic one pot chicken
directions: Combine chicken, stock, lime juice, fish sauce, lemongrass, ginger, garlic and mushrooms in a 4.5-quart slow cooker. Cook, covered, on low, for 6 hours.
Add bok choy and cook, covered, for 30 mins, or until bok choy is tender. Serve chicken mixture topped with remaining ingredients.

title: pavlova roulade with passionfruit and lime syrup
directions: For the syrup, place passionfruit pulp, sugar, lime peel and juice, and 2 tbsp water in small saucepan on medium-high heat. Bring to a boil; boil for 8 mins, or until syrupy. Remove from heat. Transfer to small bowl and cool slightly. Refrigerate until cold.

Preheat the oven to 350°F. Line a baking pan with parchment paper. For the roulade, rub lemon wedge around inside of large bowl and over whisk attachment of electric mixer (this helps to stabilize the egg whites and add volume). Whisk egg whites until foamy. Gradually add sugar, whisking until all sugar is absorbed and meringue is thick and glossy.
Spread meringue evenly on prepared pan to a 12 x 8 inch rectangle. Bake for 20 mins. Turn off oven and leave meringue inside to cool for 30 mins. Remove from oven. Cool completely.
Beat the cream and vanilla in a medium bowl with an electric mixer until stiff peaks form. Place a sheet of parchment paper on top of cooled meringue and invert so underside is on top.

Arrange banana slices on meringue, then top with the whipped cream. Fold meringue over on itself lengthwise to form a long roll, pulling off parchment paper as you go. Place on a serving platter, seam-side down. Discard paper.
Drizzle with syrup and sprinkle with strawberries.

title: autumn soup with pesto crostini
directions: Preheat oven to 450°F. Line a shallow baking tray with parchment paper. Arrange tomatoes, cut-side up, in prepared tray. Sprinkle with flaky sea salt, sugar and a little fresh black pepper. Sprinkle with lemon zest then drizzle with olive oil. Roast for 30 mins, until collapsed and lightly charred. When cool enough to handle, peel, discarding peels.

Char peppers over an open flame or under a broiler. When completely blackened, transfer to a plate, cover with plastic wrap and set aside to cool. Remove charred skin then cut peppers in 1/2. Remove cores and seeds. Chop coarsely.

Heat olive oil in a medium saucepan over medium heat. Cook garlic for 1 min, until just starting to brown. Add tomato puree and 2 cups water. Bring to a gentle boil then lower heat, partially cover and cook for 20 mins.
Add green beans and pepper to soup. Cook for 15 mins, partially covered. Add peeled tomatoes and zucchini. Cook for 2-3 mins. Season.

Meanwhile, to make the pesto crostini, reduce oven to 350°F. Brush bread with olive oil. Arrange on a baking tray and bake for 5-7 mins, or until golden brown. Top crostini with garlic, basil, pine nuts and Parmesan. Drizzle with extra virgin olive oil.
Serve soup with pesto crostini.

title: persian citrus rice pudding
directions: Place the milk, 2 tbsp sugar, vanilla seeds and a pinch of salt in a saucepan. Bring to a boil then mix in the rice, lemon zest and orange zest. Cover and gently heat for 25-30 mins, stirring occasionally.
Gently heat the orange liqueur then add the saffron and rose water. Leave to steep for 10 mins.
Mix the gelatin into the rice pudding and stir well until dissolved. Mix in the rose water and saffron infusion. Remove from the heat and set aside to cool for 10-15 mins.
Beat the egg whites until stuff while trickling in the rest of the sugar. Fold into the warm rice pudding. Set aside to cool completely.

Whip the cream until stiff then fold into the rice pudding. Divide between 4 ramekins. Sprinkle with rose petals then cover and chill for 3 hours. Serve with rose petals, sliced figs and a drizzle of orange juice.

title: christmas kisses shortbread biscuits
directions: Combine 2/3 cup powdered sugar, butter, flour and egg in a mixing bowl. With a pastry knife or fork, combine into a smooth dough (you may need to use your fingers to finish bringing it together). Form dough into a ball, wrap in plastic wrap and chill for 30 mins.

Preheat oven to 350°F. Remove dough from plastic wrap and shape into 16 balls. Press balls flat then place a chocolate kiss in the center of each disc. Fold extra dough over chocolate and shape back into a ball. Transfer to a baking tray lined with parchment paper and bake for 15 mins. Let cool for 5 mins then dust with remaining powdered sugar. Transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.

title: meatlover's pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Lightly grease a pizza or baking tray.

Place pizza base on prepared tray. Spread barbecue sauce over top then sprinkle with 1/2 the cheese. Top with steak, bacon, salami, chicken and onion. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake for 10-15 mins, until cheese is golden and base is crisp.
Sprinkle with parsley and cut into wedges to serve.

title: garlic vegetable fritters
directions: Mix the chickpea flour, salt, baking powder, cumin, and chili powder together in a bowl. Gradually stir in 1 cup plus 1 tbsp cold water until a thick batter forms. Stir in the garlic.

Heat the oil in a large pan until it reaches 350°F, or until it shimmers. Pull the vegetable pieces through the batter until fully coated then lower each piece into the oil. Fry for 2-4 mins (depending on the size of the vegetable), until golden and crisp. Drain on paper towels then serve with pickles.

title: chicken and zucchini risotto
directions: Heat 1 tbsp of the oil in a large skillet on medium-high heat. Add the chicken and saute for 3-4 mins until browned. Transfer to a plate. Add remaining 1 tbsp oil and 2 tbsp butter to same skillet. Add onion and garlic and saute for 2-3 mins until tender. Add rice and stir to coat.

Add wine and simmer for 2-3 mins until absorbed. Transfer mixture to rice cooker. Add stock and chicken, stirring. Season to taste. Turn rice cooker on to "cook" mode. When rice is cooked, leave on "warm" mode for 10 mins.

Meanwhile, heat remaining 2 tbsp butter in the skillet on medium heat. Add the zucchini and saute for 4-5 mins until golden and tender. When ready to serve, stir zucchini, peas, parsley and lemon peel into risotto. Serve topped with shaved Parmesan cheese and additional parsley leaves.

title: irish coffee with florentines
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper. For the florentines, mix corn flakes, cherries, raisins, almonds and condensed milk in a bowl. Drop rounded spoonfuls of mixture onto prepared pans, allowing room for spreading.
Bake for 10-12 mins or until light golden brown. Cool in pans on wire racks.

Meanwhile, melt chocolate in a bowl over a saucepan of simmering water (do not let bowl touch water). Remove bowl from pan. Cool slightly. Spread chocolate on flat side of each florentine. Using a fork, create lines in chocolate. Place, chocolate-side up, on a wire rack to set.
For the Irish coffee, pour coffee into 2 heatproof serving glasses. Add whiskey and sugar; stir to combine. Top with whipped cream. Serve with florentines.

title: green chili stew
directions: Heat half of the oil in large ovenproof skillet on high heat. Cook steak, in batches, stirring, until browned all over. Remove from skillet.
Preheat the oven to 350°F.
Heat remaining oil in same skillet. Cook onion, garlic, cumin and chili pepper, stirring, until onion softens. Add stock and tomato paste; bring to a boil, stirring. Return steak to skillet. Cover.
Bake for 45 mins. Add tomato and potato; cover and bake for 35 mins. Uncover; bake 20 mins.
Meanwhile, cut each tortilla into six wedges. Place, in single layer, on baking pan. Toast in oven about 8 mins or until crisp.
Stir cilantro into stew. Serve with tortilla crisps.

title: tuna, roast pepper and pesto pizzas
directions: Preheat the oven to 450°F. Line a large baking pan with parchment paper.
Place pizza crusts on prepared pan. Spread evenly with pesto. Top with tuna and peppers. Sprinkle with mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 10 mins or until crust is crisp. Top with arugula; drizzle with oil. Season with salt and pepper and serve.

title: greek salad
directions: Whisk together vinegar, parsley, garlic and oregano. Gradually whisk in olive oil until emulsified. Season and set aside.
Toss remaining ingredients together then arrange on a serving platter. Drizzle with vinaigrette just before serving.

title: fields of play cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Grease a deep 14 x 10-inch baking pan; line bottom and sides with parchment paper, extending paper 2 inches above sides for handles.

Prepare cake mixes according to package directions. Spread mixture in prepared pan. Bake for 1 hour, or until a skewer inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 mins. Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack.

For the buttercream, beat butter with an electric mixer until the butter is as white as possible (this will result in a whiter buttercream which will give you better results if coloring it). Gradually beat in half the sifted powdered sugar, then the milk, then the remaining powdered sugar. Beat until buttercream is smooth and spreadable. Keep scraping down the side of the bowl during beating.
Level cake top. Secure cake, cut-side down, on cake board, with a little buttercream. Tint remaining buttercream green with food color; spread all over cake.
Combine granulated sugar and food color in small plastic bag. Rub together until sugar is evenly colored. Sprinkle top of cake with green sugar.

To decorate, use white decorating gel to pipe lines on field, using picture as a guide. Pipe black decorating gel around lollipop sticks for corner posts. Wrap thin strips of red fruit roll-ups around lollipop sticks for goal posts.
Decorate with toy balls, equipment and goal posts, as desired.

title: apple, carrot and ginger juice
directions: Push the carrot, celery, apple and ginger through a juice extractor into a glass.
Stir in 2 tbsp water and lemon juice and serve.

title: pork schnitzels with waldorf salad
directions: To make the salad, combine celery, apples, nuts and parsley. Toss with mayonnaise and yogurt. Season.
For the pork schnitzels, combine breadcrumbs, Parmesan and sage. Season. Coat pork in flour, shaking off excess. Dip in egg then coat in breadcrumb mixture. Chill for 20 mins.
Heat oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. Cook schnitzels for 3-4 mins per side, until golden and cooked through. Drain on paper towels. Serve with salad.

title: fried fish with bacon mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water for 20 mins. Meanwhile, cut fish into pieces, season and dredge in flour.

Heat butter in a frying pan and saute bacon. Add onion and thyme and saute briefly. Stir in lettuce then remove from heat. Heat oil in a large frying pan and fry fish skin side down, until golden brown. Turn and briefly fry other side.
Drain potatoes, and mash to a puree with milk. Fold in bacon mixture. Season with salt and nutmeg. Drain fish on paper towels. Serve with the mashed potatoes.

title: crusted baked cod with tomato, caper and olive sauce
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Place bread, Parmesan cheese and basil in food processor and pulse to combine. With motor running, add oil until well incorporated. Season with salt and black pepper.
Place tomato puree, sugar, garlic, capers, oregano and olives in baking dish. Stir to combine. Season with salt and black pepper to taste.
Season fish with salt and black pepper and place on top of sauce. Press breadcrumb mixture over each fillet.
Bake for 20 mins, or until fish is just cooked and breadcrumbs are golden. Remove fish from oven and sprinkle with additional basil. Serve with crusty bread and vegetables or green salad.

title: roasted beet and garlic salad with goat cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Place 12 beets and half of garlic on a piece of foil. Drizzle with olive oil. Fold edges in to form a sealed parcel. Repeat with remaining beets and garlic. Place parcels on a baking sheet and cook 1 hour, or until beets are tender. Remove from oven. When cool enough to handle, peel beets and place in a bowl.

For the dressing, squeeze roasted garlic from skins into a mortar. Add a pinch of salt and grind with pestle until smooth. Add vinegar and stir well to combine. Slowly drizzle in half the oil, grinding, and season to taste.
To assemble, add dressing to bowl with beets and toss to combine. Spread arugula on a large serving platter and top with beets and goat cheese. Drizzle with remaining oil, season and serve.

title: caramel apple crumble cheesecake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Grease a foil-lined 9-inch square baking pan, with foil extending at 2 opposite sides for handles. For the cake, beat butter and 1/4 cup sugar in a large bowl with an electric mixer until creamy. Beat in egg yolks one at a time. Fold in flour and baking powder. Stir in milk.
Beat egg whites in medium bowl with electric mixer until stiff peaks form, adding 1 tsp sugar in a trickle. Gently fold egg whites into cake batter. Spoon into prepared pan. Bake for 12 mins.

For the cheesecake filling, beat cream cheese, sour cream, sugar, eggs, cornstarch and caramel topping in large bowl until smooth. Remove cake from oven. Spread with the cheesecake filling. Bake for 15 mins.

For the apple crumble topping, mix butter, sugar, flour and egg in a medium bowl. Remove cheesecake from oven. Sprinkle with grated apple and the crumble topping. Bake for 20 mins. Cool cake in pan on a wire rack. Dust with powdered sugar and cut into squares to serve.

title: sweet potato and pecan loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 325°F. Grease an 8x5 inch loaf pan. Line base and long sides with parchment paper, extending paper 3/4 inch over sides.

Beat butter, sugar and eggs until just combined. Fold in nuts, coconut and mashed sweet potato. Stir in flour and milk, in 2 batches. Transfer to prepared pan and bake for 1 hour 40 mins, or until a skewer inserted in the center comes out clean. Let cool in pan for 10 mins then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.

title: christmas cranberry pimm's cocktail
directions: Pour Pimm's and cranberry juice into a large pitcher or bowl. Add mint, apple, orange and lemon. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Place ice and cucumber in beverage glasses. Fill 3/4 full with Pimm's and fruit mixture. Top up with lemonade.

title: combination noodle salad
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water according to package directions. Drain. Toss with half of sesame oil; set aside to cool.
For the sauce, whisk remaining sesame oil, half of vegetable oil, soy sauce, vinegar, sesame seeds and chili pepper in a small bowl. Season with freshly ground black pepper.

Heat remaining vegetable oil in a small skillet on medium heat. Add egg and swirl to coat bottom of pan. Cook 30 seconds until set; turn and cook other side. Transfer to a cutting board. Roll up and cut into thin strips.
Place noodles in a serving bowl. Top with pork, ham, cucumber and shrimp. Add sauce and toss well. Serve topped with omelet and ginger.

title: frozen black forest trifle
directions: Cut cake in half horizontally. Place bottom half (without icing) in an 8-inch springform pan. (Freeze remaining half to use in another recipe.) Flatten cake to cover base of pan.
Coarsely chop cherries. Sprinkle half the cherries over cake. Drizzle with 2 tablespoons of the reserved syrup.
Place custard in a bowl. Fold in a third of the whipped cream. Spread custard mixture over cherries; level surface. Freeze 1 hour.
Meanwhile, place cornstarch in a small saucepan; whisk in remaining syrup. Heat over moderate heat. Cook, stirring, 3 minutes or until mixture boils and thickens slightly. Cool.

Using an electric mixer, beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in a bowl until smooth and combined. Fold in remaining whipped cream, then remaining cherries. Spoon cream cheese mixture over chocolate custard layer; level surface. Drizzle with cooled cherry sauce. Using a skewer, swirl cherry sauce into cream cheese mixture. Freeze 6 hours or until firm. Serve topped with chocolate curls.

title: baked savory ricotta tart
directions: Place flour and butter in a food processor. Pulse until combined (mixture will be lumpy). Add sour cream and pulse until dough comes together. Turn onto a lightly floured surface. Knead into a flat disc. Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate for 20 mins.
Preheat the oven to 400°F. Lightly grease a 10 x 6-inch baking pan.
Roll out pastry on lightly floured surface to form a 12 x 8-inch rectangle. Press pastry into bottom and sides of prepared pan, trimming edges. Refrigerate for 30 mins.
Line crust with parchment paper and fill with dried beans or rice. Bake for 15 mins. Remove the paper and beans and bake for a further 10 mins. Reduce oven temperature to 350°F.

Whisk eggs, cream and ricotta in a large bowl until smooth. Season to taste. Pour into crust. Bake for 25-30 mins, until set and golden. Allow to cool slightly then sprinkle with arugula leaves. Cut into slices to serve.

title: mini orange-polenta cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Line 30 holes of 3 mini muffin pans with paper liners.
Process almonds until finely chopped. Set aside. Process orange until pulpy. Add to ground almonds.

Cream butter, sugar and egg until thick and creamy. Fold in polenta and baking powder then almond-orange mixture. Distribute between paper liners and bake for 17-20 mins, or until a skewer, inserted in the center, comes out clean. Let cool for 5 mins before transferring to a wire rack to cool.
For the icing, combine powdered sugar, orange zest and enough orange juice to form a thin icing. Drizzle over cupcakes and decorate with sugar roses.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Whip egg whites until stiff, gradually adding 1/4 cup sugar. Add egg yolks and 1 tsp vanilla then fold in flour and baking powder. Transfer to a 10 inch cake pan, smooth and bake for 15 mins until golden brown. Remove from oven and let cool in the pan.

Bloom gelatin in cold water to soften. Mix cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tsp vanilla extract and lemon juice. If using sheet gelatin, squeeze out excess water. Combine bloomed gelatin and 3 tbsp cream cheese mixture and gently heat until gelatin melts. Mix with main cream cheese mixture. Whip cream until stiff then fold in. Spread over cooled cake and chill for 1 hour. Top with 1 1/4 lb strawberries and chill for 2 hours.
Heat remaining sugar with 3/4 cup water and heat until dissolved. Drizzle over cake then chill for 1 hour.
To serve, puree remaining strawberries with powdered sugar. Remove cake from pan and place on serving plate. Drizzle strawberry puree over top.

title: chocolate fudge bars with raisins and pecans
directions: Line a 7x11 inch rimmed baking pan with parchment paper.

Melt butter and honey in a saucepan over medium heat. Add raisins and sugar. Bring to a boil then remove from heat and let cool slightly. Whisk in egg. Combine crushed cookies, pecans and dark chocolate then mix in butter mixture. Press firmly into prepared pan and chill for 30 mins, until firm.
Meanwhile, to make the topping, melt chocolate and shortening in a saucepan over low heat, until melted and smooth. Spread over chilled bars. Chill until firm. Cut into squares to serve.

title: greek style mini spring lamb roasts
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Place potatoes, garlic cloves and fresh oregano in a baking pan. Drizzle with 3 tbsp of the oil and toss to coat. Roast on top rack of oven for 30 mins.
Meanwhile, mix crushed garlic, dried oregano, rosemary, lemon peel, salt, pepper and remaining 1 1/2 tbsp oil in a bowl. Add lamb and turn to coat. Place in a baking pan.
Remove potatoes from oven; turn and crush lightly using back of spoon. Return to top rack of oven. Place lamb on middle rack and roast for 20-25 mins, for medium, or until cooked to desired doneness.

Remove lamb from oven. Let stand, loosely covered with foil, for 10 mins. Increase oven temp to 475°F. Roast potatoes for 10 mins or until crisp. Remove potatoes from oven and season with salt and pepper.
Carve lamb and serve with roast potatoes and green salad.

title: marinated salmon with fava bean purée
directions: Blanch the fava beans in boiling water for 30 seconds. Drain and rinse under cold water. Remove the skins then place in a saucepan with the stock and cook for 10 mins. Drain, reserving the stock.
For the salmon, mix 1/2 the herbs with 2 tbsp lemon juice, 1 tbsp oil and 1 tsp pink peppercorns. Add the salmon and coat. Chill for 1 hour.
Place the fava beans, garlic, 1 tbsp oil and 1/2-3/4 cups stock in the blender. Add the remaining herbs and puree. Season and add lemon juice, to taste. Chill for 45 mins.
Beat the cream cheese until creamy. Line 6 serving glasses with the salmon and top with the bean puree and 1 tbsp cream cheese. Sprinkle with the remaining herbs and pink peppercorns.

title: sweet potato and lentil curry
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan over high heat. Saute onion for 3-4 mins, until tender. Add cumin, mustard seeds, garlic and curry leaves. Cook for 1-2 mins, until fragrant. Add stock, sweet potato, 2 cups water, tomatoes, lentils and chili. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 35-40 mins, until vegetables are tender. Add spinach and simmer for 1-2 mins, until wilted. Remove from heat and add basil.
Serve curry with rice. Garnish with sliced almonds and basil. Serve papadums and yogurt on the side.

title: roast chicken drumsticks with glazed shallots
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F. Heat oil in a large frying pan on medium. Add shallots and cook for 6-7 minutes, shaking pan frequently, until pale golden.
Sprinkle with sugar and cook for another 3 minutes, until lightly caramelized. Transfer to a baking dish.
Add chicken drumsticks, stock, wine, thyme and pepper to baking dish. Combine well and cover dish with foil. Bake for 30 minutes, stirring once.
Remove foil and cook for another 10 minutes, basting and turning chicken once or twice. Transfer chicken and shallots to a serving dish and keep warm.
Strain cooking liquid into a saucepan and simmer for 5 minutes, until slightly reduced. Season to taste and spoon over chicken. Serve immediately.

title: pork tenderloin with crispy sage and capers
directions: Heat 2 tbsp olive oil in a large frying pan over high heat. Fry sage leaves for 1 min, or until crispy. Drain on paper towels and season.

Drain off oil, leaving 1 tbsp in pan. Season pork generously then cook for 3 mins per side over high heat. Reduce heat and cook for 4 mins. Remove from pan and let rest for 3 mins. Cut into thick slices.
Meanwhile, cook tomatoes, cut-sides down, for 3 mins. Remove and set aside.

Clean pan, add remaining oil and cook capers over medium heat. Whisk in lemon juice and butter. Season to taste. Arrange pork and tomatoes on serving plates, pour caper sauce over top and sprinkle with fried sage leaves. Serve with sugar snap peas.

title: strawberries with vanilla ricotta
directions: Place strawberries in a bowl. Sprinkle with 1 tbsp of the powdered sugar and drizzle with cognac or balsamic vinegar.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 30 mins.
Combine ricotta, yogurt and remaining 1 tbsp powdered sugar in a small bowl. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Divide strawberries among serving bowls. Top with a dollop of ricotta mixture and serve with biscotti or almond bread.

title: beer bread
directions: Heat the beer until lukewarm. Add the honey and crumble in the yeast, stirring to dissolve it. Mix the flours and salt in a large bowl. Add the beer mixture and knead for about 10 minutes until smooth. Cover and let stand in a warm place for about 1 hour.
When doubled in size, knead again for 1 minute to deflate. Shape into an oval and place on a baking sheet. Cover and let stand for about 30 minutes.
Preheat the oven to 425°F. Bake for about 35 min. Cool on a wire rack.

title: spaghetti with avocado, feta and shrimp
directions: Combine feta and sour cream in a bowl and mix well. Puree avocado and lemon juice in a blender, season, and stir into the feta cream.

Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water according to package instructions. Meanwhile, heat oil in a large frying pan and saute shrimp for 2 mins. Add garlic and chili and saute for another 2 mins. Season to taste.

Drain spaghetti and return to saucepan. Stir three quarters of the sauce into the pasta and add the shrimp mixture. Divide among 4 bowls, top with remaining sauce and garnish with finely sliced chili.

title: chili rubbed hickory smoked ribeye steaks
directions: Combine lemon zest, chili powder, thyme, paprika, olive oil and garlic in a large bowl. Add beef and turn to coat in mixture. Cover and chill for 3 hours or overnight.
Soak wood chips in 2 cups water in a medium bowl. Let stand for 3 hours or overnight.
Place drained chips in a smoke box and beef on a grill plate. Grill beef over indirect heat, covered, for 10 mins, or until cooked to your liking.

title: chicken and pea yellow curry
directions: Heat the oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Saute the onion for 2-3 mins, until softened. Stir in the chicken pieces and curry paste and cook, stirring, for 5 mins or until lightly browned.
Add the stock and potatoes and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 20 mins, until the potatoes are tender and the chicken is cooked through.
Stir in the coconut milk and peas and simmer for 5 mins. Top with the cilantro and serve with steamed rice and pappadums.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan on medium heat. Cook fennel, carrot and celery for 5 mins, until golden and softened. Stir in tomatoes, stock, beans and 2 cups water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer for 10 mins, until vegetables are soft.
Stir in breadcrumbs. Ladle into serving bowls. Top with a dollop of pesto and sprinkle with shaved Parmesan cheese. Serve with crusty bread.

title: double chocolate bar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Line a 9x9 inch baking pan with foil and coat with cooking spray.

In a food processor, combine granola, 2 cups chocolate chips and brown sugar. Process for 30 seconds. Add butter and pulse 12 times. Transfer to prepared pan and firmly press into base. Bake for 10 mins. Let cool then chill for 1 hour.
Meanwhile, beat cream cheese until smooth. Gradually add milk then pudding mix. Whisk for 1 min, or until thick. Spread over granola base and chill for 30 mins.

In a medium saucepan, heat heavy cream until almost boiling. Remove from heat and add remaining chocolate chips. Let stand for 5 mins then whisk until smooth. Let cool for 5 mins then pour over white chocolate layer. Chill for 30 mins, or until set.
Remove from pan and cut into bars. Pipe a red bow using red colored frosting onto each bar.

title: corn fritters with smoked salmon
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, paprika and salt into a medium bowl. Gradually whisk in egg and milk until smooth. Stir in corn, onions and cilantro. Season.
Lightly oil a large frying pan and place over medium heat. Working in batches, drop 1 tbsp batter for each fritter into pan and cook until browned lightly on both sides.
Serve fritters topped with avocado and smoked salmon.

title: caramel apple puddings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Lightly grease a 6-cup muffin pan. Whisk eggs, brown sugar and vanilla together until pale and creamy. Add flour and butter. Fold in chopped apple. Transfer to prepared pan. Place 1 apple slice on top of each pudding and bake for 20-25 mins. Let cool in pan for 5 mins.

Meanwhile, to make caramel, combine sugar and 1/3 cup water. Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves. Increase heat to medium and simmer, without stirring, for 8-10 mins, until pale golden brown. Gradually add cream.
Remove puddings from pan. Spoon sauce over top and serve with whipped cream.

title: tandoori chicken salad with spiced yogurt
directions: Combine paste and yogurt in a bowl. Add chicken and turn to coat.
For the spiced yogurt, combine all ingredients in a small bowl. Season to taste.
Heat oil in a large skillet on medium heat. Season chicken. Cook, in batches, for 5 mins, or until browned all over and just cooked through.
Place chicken in a serving bowl. Add spinach, cucumber, tomatoes and mint; toss to combine. Drizzle with spiced yogurt and serve.

title: mediterranean roasted vegetable tart tatin
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°F. Spread the vegetables in a single layer across the bottom of a large baking dish - use a second dish if necessary.
Toss with the oil and rosemary leaves. Roast for 15-20 mins until beginning to soften and char.
Lightly grease a 10-inch round spring form pan. Line with wax paper or parchment. Roll out the pie crust on a lightly floured surface to a rough circle just larger than the pan.
Transfer the vegetables to the prepared pan. Press down with the back of a spoon to roughly level the surface.

Place the pie crust over the top. Press into the vegetables; fold the overhanging pastry into the pan to form a thicker edge at the sides. Prick all over with a fork. Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese.
Return to the oven. Bake for 15-20 mins until the crust is golden and cooked through. Carefully, invert the pan; release the sides; pull away the wax paper. Serve the vegetable tart hot in wedges.

title: smoked salmon, tomato and feta pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°F. Lightly grease 2 pizza trays. Place bases on prepared trays. Spread pasta sauce evenly over each base. Bake for 10 mins, or until light golden brown.

Top with tomatoes, squid, salmon, pizza cheese, onion and feta. Bake for 8-10 mins, or until squid is cooked through and bases are crispy. Sprinkle with parsley and chili. Cut into wedges and serve with lemon wedges.

title: manhattan cocktail
directions: Mix the whisky, sweet vermouth and angostura bitters. Stir then pour into a cocktail glass and garnish with a cocktail cherry.

title: barley pilaf with pumpkin and feta
directions: Heat 1 tbsp each oil and butter in a medium saucepan on medium heat. Cook onion and garlic for 7-10 mins until translucent and tender.

Add pearl barley; cook for 1 min, stirring. Add chicken stock, 1 1/4 cups water and canned tomatoes. Bring to a gentle boil. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 40 mins, or until the pearl barley is tender but retaining a little chewiness. Season with 1/2 tsp salt.

Heat the remaining oil and butter in a medium skillet on medium-low heat. Add the pumpkin; cover and cook for about 15 mins or until just tender, tossing carefully once or twice during cooking. Stir in the rosemary towards the end of the cooking time.
Ladle the pearl barley into hot bowls. Top with the pumpkin and feta. Dust with paprika and serve.

title: raspberry and ricotta tart
directions: Place flour, 2 tbsp sugar, lemon zest and butter in a food processor. Pulse until mixture resembles breadcrumbs.

With motor running, gradually add enough iced water (about 1 tbsp) so mixture forms a ball. Turn out on to a lightly floured surface and bring dough together. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill for 30 mins.
Preheat oven to 350°F. Lightly grease a 9 inch tart pan.

Place dough on a lightly floured surface and roll out to 1/8 inch thick. Ease into prepared pan and trim edges. Chill for 20 mins. Line with parchment paper and pie weights. Blind-bake for 15 mins. Remove paper and weights and bake for 10 mins.
Meanwhile, beat ricotta, cream, 1/4 cup sugar, eggs and vanilla extract together until smooth. Pour into tart crust and bake for 30 mins, or until just set. Refrigerate until cold.
Arrange raspberries over tart to serve.

title: spicy squash rice cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Toss squash with 1 tbsp oil. Arrange on a baking tray and season to taste. Bake for 15-20 mins, until golden and tender.

Meanwhile, heat 1 tbsp oil in a large saucepan over high heat. Saute onion and garlic for 3-4 mins, until onion is tender. Add rice and chili flakes. Cook, stirring, for 1 min. Add hot stock to rice mixture, 1 cup at a time, stirring until all liquid has absorbed and rice is tender, about 20 mins.
Add cheese, peas, cilantro and squash mixture to rice. Transfer to a large bowl. Let cool then chill until cold and firm.
Roll tablespoonfuls of risotto mixture into balls. Flatten slightly then toss in seasoned flour.
Heat remaining oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. Working in batches, cook risotto cakes for 2-3 mins per side, until golden brown.
Serve with lemon mayonnaise.

title: baked chocolate custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.
Whisk eggs, cocoa powder and sugar together in a large bowl.

Heat milk in a small saucepan. Gradually whisk into egg mixture. Transfer mixture to 4 - 6 oz ramekins. Place in a baking dish and add enough water to come halfway up sides of dishes. Bake for 45 mins, or until just set. Dust with powdered sugar just before serving.

title: orange and cognac fizz
directions: Add 2 tbsp each of orange liqueur and cognac to two cocktail glasses. Add half the grenadine to each glass then top up with champagne. Stir once then serve garnished with kumquat slices.

title: pear and passionfruit pastries
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°F. Lightly grease and line a baking pan with parchment paper.

Cut each pastry sheet into 4 equal squares. Place a heaping tablespoon pear and a teaspoon passionfruit in center of each square. Brush edges of pastry lightly with water. Fold corners into center over filling, pinching edges to seal. Arrange on prepared pan.
Bake 20-25 mins, until puffed and golden. Serve topped with remaining pulp. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: strawberries and cream powder puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease 2 - 12-cup shallow patty pans or muffin pans.
Whip eggs for about 5 mins, until thick and creamy. Gradually add sugar, beating well after each addition, or until sugar is dissolved.

Sift cornstarch and flour together 3 times. Gently fold into egg mixture. Distribute between pans and bake for 12 mins, or until cakes spring back when touched lightly in the center. Turn out onto a wire rack to cool completely.
Beat heavy cream and powdered sugar to soft peaks. Fold in strawberries. Sandwich sponge cakes together with cream mixture and dust with extra powdered sugar.

title: blast off cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease and flour 2 cake pans.
Make cake mix according to package directions. Distribute between prepared pans and bake for 50 mins. Let cool in pans for 10 mins then transfer to wire racks to cool completely.

Meanwhile, to make the buttercream, beat butter until as white as possible. Gradually beat in 1/2 the powdered sugar and milk then remaining powdered sugar. Beat until smooth. Tint purple with food coloring.

Place cakes side by side then use a serrated knife to level tops and trim to resemble a rocket shape. Secure cakes to a cake board with a little buttercream then coat with remaining buttercream. Decorate with jelly beans and place sparklers in cake.
Light sparklers just before serving.

title: blueberry and walnut teacake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease and line a deep, 8-inch cake pan.
In a large bowl, using an electric mixer, cream softened butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in vanilla extract.
Sift flours together. Fold lightly into creamed mixture alternately with sour cream and zest, until well combined. Fold in berries and nuts.
Spread mixture into cake pan. Bake for 35-40 mins, until cooked when tested. Cool cake in pan for 5 mins before turning out onto a wire rack.
Brush top with melted butter and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar while hot. Cool before serving.

title: pumpkin, halloumi and pea couscous
directions: Preheat oven 350°F. Line a roasting pan with parchment paper. Add onion, pumpkin, garlic and chili to the pan. Drizzle with 1/4 cup oil; toss gently to combine. Bake, stirring occasionally, for 20-25 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

Meanwhile, place couscous in a medium heatproof bowl. Bring stock to a boil and stir in to couscous. Cover with plastic wrap; set aside for 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed. Using a fork, fluff and separate grains. Allow to cool to room temperature. Add peas, spices and roasted vegetables; mix well.
Heat remaining oil in a medium frying pan over moderate heat. Cook halloumi, turning, for 2-3 minutes or until golden brown. Add to couscous mixture; stir to combine.
Spoon couscous into shallow serving bowls. Serve with lemon wedges.

title: kumquat and ginger marmalade
directions: Place kumquat seeds in small bowl with 1 cup water. Let stand overnight. Combine kumquat slices with 6 cups water in a large bowl. Cover and let stand overnight.

Strain seeds, reserving liquid (this now contains pectin, which contributes to the setting of the jam); discard seeds. Place kumquat mixture into large saucepan with reserved liquid. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer, covered, for 30 mins, or until kumquats are tender. Add sugar; stir constantly, without boiling, until sugar has dissolved (mixture should not be more than 2 inches deep).

Bring to a boil on high heat. Boil rapidly for 15 mins without stirring, or until a teaspoon of mixture gels when tested. (To test for a jam's setting point, place a small quantity of the mixture onto a saucer. Allow to cool. If its ready, it will gel and wrinkle when moved. Remove pan from heat while testing.)
Stir in ginger; let stand for 10 mins. Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal immediately. Store in a cool dry place. Once opened, store in the refrigerator.

title: shrimp and avocado salad with ginger dressing
directions: Combine shrimp, snow peas, chives, spinach and avocado in a large bowl.
To make the ginger dressing, press grated ginger between 2 spoons set over a medium bowl. Reserve juice in bowl, discard ginger solids. Whisk in olive oil, lemon juice and sugar. Season.
Just before serving, pour dressing over salad and toss to combine. Season.

title: couscous-crusted chicken with harissa yogurt
directions: Bring stock or water to a boil in a saucepan. Place couscous in a bowl and pour in hot stock or water. Cover with plastic wrap and let stand 5 mins. Fluff with a fork to separate. Stir in herbs and 3/4 of zest.
Coat chicken pieces in flour. Dip into combined egg and milk. Coat well with couscous mixture and chill for 15 mins.

Meanwhile, for the harissa yogurt, heat 2 tbsp oil in a frying pan on high. Saute pepper, chili pepper and garlic for 4-5 mins until tender. Place mixture in a food processor with remaining olive oil and process until smooth. Stir in yogurt and transfer to a serving bowl.

Heat vegetable oil in same cleaned frying pan on high. Fry chicken in batches for 2-3 mins each side, until golden and cooked. Drain on paper towels. Top with remaining zest and mint leaves, to serve, and accompany with the harissa yogurt.

title: lemon and lime mousse
directions: Combine citrus zest and juice with cream. Whip to soft peaks. Whip egg whites to soft peaks then gradually whisk in sugar, beating until thick and glossy. Fold into whipped cream. Spoon into 4 tall serving glasses and chill until ready to serve.
Sprinkle with pistachios to decorate.

title: duck with indonesian style noodles
directions: Prepare noodles following packet instructions. Drain well and place in a large bowl and allow to cool.
Mix in the duck and sprouts. Top with hard-boiled egg and nuts and serve.

title: pork and bean hot pot
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet on medium-high. Brown pork in batches for 3-4 mins. Remove and set aside.
Add onion to pan and cook on low heat for 4 mins, stirring, until softened. Add paprika and garlic and cook, stirring, for 1 min.
Add pork, green beans, carrot and stock. Increase heat to medium-high. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 15 mins, or until pork is tender.
Add cannellini beans and tomatoes and cook for 3-4 mins, until heated through. Season. Spoon into bowls. Garnish with cilantro leaves and serve with bread.

title: clam and mussel chowder
directions: Melt the butter in a saucepan and saute the garlic and leeks until softened. Add the clams and mussels and saute for 5 mins. Add the wine and stock, cover and simmer for 12 mins.

Drain and set aside the clams, mussels and leeks, reserving the stock and returning it to the pan. Stir in the cream and bring to a boil. Add the crab paste and stir until melted. Simmer over a low heat for 5 mins. Return the clams, mussels and leeks to the pan and season with salt, black pepper and a dash of lemon juice.
Ladle into bowls and garnish with parsley and lemon slices. Serve with garlic and herb bread.

title: garlic chicken and broad beans
directions: Heat oil in a heavy-based saucepan on high. Cook chicken for 3 minutes each side, until browned. Remove from pan and discard oil.

Melt butter on medium heat. Pan-fry shallots for 3 minutes, until soft. Return chicken to pan and add wine. Bring to a boil and cook for 4 minutes, until wine evaporates. Add stock and simmer, covered, on low heat for 30 minutes, until chicken is cooked through.
Meanwhile, cook broad beans in a saucepan of boiling, salted water for 2 minutes. Drain. Cool in ice water. Drain again. Remove and discard skins.
Remove chicken. Stir in cream, garlic and broad beans. Bring to a boil and season to taste. Serve chicken with broad beans and sauce.

title: caramelized onions
directions: In a heavy-bottomed saucepan, heat oil and butter over medium heat. Cook onions and garlic for 12-15 mins, stirring often, until onions have softened and are golden brown. Reduce heat to low and add sugar, vinegar and thyme. Cook, stirring occasionally, for 15-20 mins, until mixture thickens to a jam-like consistency. Remove from heat and season to taste.

title: veal and bacon meatballs with salsa and potato wedges
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Place the potato wedges on a baking sheet and drizzle with 3 tbsp of the oil. Season with salt and freshly ground black pepper and cook for 35-45 mins.
To make the salsa, mix together the tomatoes, spring onions, 4 tbsp oil and the lemon juice in a bowl. Season and add the sugar, to taste. Chill until ready to serve.

For the meatballs, mix together the grated potatoes, veal, cottage cheese, oregano, salt and pepper. Shape into 12 balls and wrap each in a strip of bacon. Heat the remaining oil in a large frying pan, add the meatballs and brown for 4-5 mins, turning. Remove from the pan and cook on the baking sheet with the potato wedges for the last 10 mins of their cooking time. Serve the meatballs and potato wedges with the salsa and garnish with the extra oregano.

title: pork stir fry with chili and basil
directions: Heat the oil in a large wok or frying pan and add the ground pork. Cook over high heat 6-8 mins, stirring, until browned. Add the spring onion, garlic, ginger and chili pepper. Stir-fry 2-3 mins. Add the oyster and fish sauce, sugar and 6 tbsp water. Bring to a boil, stirring, and simmer 1 min until sauce thickens slightly. Stir in the basil and cilantro and serve with the rice noodles.

title: chili prawns with mango
directions: For the dressing mix together the vinegar, lime juice, mint, sugar and a little seasoning.
Heat the oil in a frying pan and fry the prawns, turning once until pink on all sides. Add the chili powder and saute for 30 seconds.
Spoon the mango onto serving plates and arrange the prawns on top. Garnish with mint sprigs and green onions and spoon the dressing over to serve.

title: crème brûléemango bars
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Grease a 15 x 12 inch baking pan. Beat the butter, vanilla extract and powdered sugar with the whisk of a mixer until creamy. Beat in the whole eggs one at a time. Sift in the flour and baking powder and mix. Spoon into the pan and smooth out. Bake for 10 mins.

In a saucepan, bring the sugar, vanilla pod and seeds and 3 3/4 cups of the milk to a boil. In a bowl, mix the cornstarch and 1/2 cup of the milk until smooth, whisk into the hot milk mixture. Simmer for 1 min, stirring, remove from the heat and remove the vanilla pod. Beat the egg yolks with 6 tbsp of the milk mixture, stir into the remaining hot milk mixture.
Remove the cake from the oven and add the diced mango. Gently spread over the milk mixture. Bake at the same temperature for 12-15 mins, until set. Remove and allow to cool.
Cut into 42 strips and sprinkle with brown sugar. Heat with a cook's torch until the sugar is golden brown and caramelized.

title: sautéed peppers and zucchini
directions: In a large frying pan, heat olive oil over medium heat. Saute shallot, peppers and zucchini until tender, about 3 mins. Add garlic, vinegar and herbs. Season and toss to combine. Arrange vegetables on a serving platter and garnish with reserved oregano.

title: tuna and macaroni mornay
directions: Preheat broiler. Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water until al dente. Drain.

Meanwhile, for the mornay sauce, melt 4 1/2 tbsp butter in a saucepan over medium heat. Stir in flour and cook, stirring, for 2 mins. Stir in milk until smooth. Increase heat and stir until sauce boils and thickens. Stir in 1/3 cup cheese and asparagus. Add nutmeg and season to taste.

Add pasta, tuna and remaining butter to sauce and toss to combine. Transfer to a baking dish and sprinkle with remaining cheese. Broil for 5 mins, or until cheese is melted and browned. Serve with salad.

title: asian pork and pineapple salad
directions: For salad base, combine pineapple, bean sprouts, pepper, mint, cilantro and cashews. Set aside.

Heat 1 tbsp oil in a wok or large frying pan over high heat, stir-fry pork and 1 clove garlic for 2 mins, until browned. Add hoisin sauce and stir-fry for 1 min. Add to salad. Whisk chili sauce, soy sauce, lemon juice and remaining peanut oil and garlic. Add to salad and toss gently. Serve.

title: creamy chicken and avocado penne
directions: Cook pasta in boiling salted water until al dente. Drain.

Meanwhile, heat oil in a large, deep frying pan over medium heat. Saute garlic for 30 seconds. Increase heat to high and add chicken. Cook, stirring, for 3-4 mins, until lightly browned. Add stock. Simmer for 1-2 mins, until reduced slightly. Add cream and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 4-5 mins, until thickened.
Add pasta and tomato to pan and toss to combine. Stir, over low heat, for 1-2 mins, to heat through. Add avocado and toss to combine.
Top with basil leaves and serve with crusty bread.

title: paprika chicken casserole
directions: Heat 2 tbsp of olive oil in a frying pan and brown the chicken over medium heat for 5-10 mins until golden brown. Heat 2 tbsp olive oil in a saucepan and saute the onions, garlic and peppers for 5 mins. Add the tomatoes and paprika and season to taste. Cover and simmer for about 10 mins.
Remove chicken legs from the frying pan and place in the tomato mixture. Add thyme, white wine and stock. Cover and simmer for 30 mins. Serve immediately with a baguette on the side.

title: watercress rösti with poached egg
directions: Heat 1 tbsp oil in a frying pan. Sweat onion for 5 mins, until softened. Remove from heat and mix with potatoes and watercress. Beat 1 egg then mix in. Add cornstarch. Season.
Heat remaining oil in the frying pan. Add large spoonfuls of potato mixture to pan and cook until golden brown on both sides. Set aside and keep warm.

Bring a saucepan of water to a boil. Add vinegar. Reduce heat to a gentle simmer. Gently slide remaining eggs into simmering water. Turn off heat, cover and set aside for 3 mins. Drain with a slotted spoon. Serve on rosti. Garnish with watercress.

title: turkey, cranberry and peanut salad
directions: Bring 6 cups water to a boil in a large saucepan. Add turkey and simmer, covered, for 35 mins, or until cooked through. Let turkey cool in poaching liquid for 15 mins. Drain turkey then shred roughly.
In a large bowl, whisk together vinegar, mustard and oil. Add turkey, cranberries, celery, bean sprouts, nuts and mint. Toss gently to combine. Serve with lettuce leaves.

title: smoked salmon, asparagus and brie omelette
directions: Melt butter in an 8 inch nonstick frying pan over medium heat. Season eggs then add to pan, tilting pan to cover base. Using a spatula, quickly draw cooked egg back from edge of pan to allow uncooked egg to run underneath.
When almost set, top with salmon, Brie, asparagus and green onion. Fold to enclose filling. Cook for 1 min, or until cheese softens. Slide onto a plate and serve with mixed greens.

title: mediterranean pork loin
directions: Cook pasta in boiling salted water according to package directions. Add zucchini 1-2 mins before pasta is finished cooking. Drain.

For the pork and tomato sauce, heat 1/2 tsp oil and sweat garlic and onion for 3-4 mins. Add chopped tomatoes, tomato paste and 4 tbsp water and simmer for 3 mins. Heat remaining oil in a separate small frying pan and sear meat for 4 mins, turning, until brown on all sides. Season, sprinkle with parsley then add tomato sauce. Bring to a boil, add olives then adjust seasoning, adding a little sugar to taste.

To finish, mix yogurt with lemon zest, season then toss with lettuce, watercress and radishes. Serve pork and tomato sauce with pasta with salad on the side. For dessert, sprinkle pears with lemon juice. Sprinkle raspberries with powdered sugar and mash. Arrange on a plate and serve.

title: madeira cake
